title: easy hawaiian chicken
directions: Place chicken in roaster pan.
In bowl, combine dressing, jam and soup mix.
Mix well and pour over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: pretzel salad (dessert)
directions: Mix strawberry jello with boiling water until dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries and mix.
Pour this over the cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: irish soda bread
directions: In large bowl, mix all dry ingredients.
Break up butter into small pieces.
Add raisins (drain water).
Slowly add milk (mixing to a gummy texture) and squeezed lemon.
Preheat oven to 350°. Place mixture in pan (grease and flour bottom only of pan).
Make a cross on top of mixture with knife.
Bake for 35 minutes until golden brown.
Let cool 10 minutes.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Spread on flour tortillas; roll up tortilla. Refrigerate overnight.
Slice next day .
(If you fill too full, they don't slice well.)

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.

title: quaker choco-oat chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars; add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in oats and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen (2 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: buttermilk dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Yields about 1 cup dip; 40 calories per tablespoon.

title: southern chocolate chip pie
directions: Divide nuts and morsels in bottom of pie crusts.
Over this, pour mixture of butter, eggs, sugar and syrup.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: nut bran muffins
directions: Combine bran, flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and nutmeg in bowl.
Mix molasses, egg, milk and butter into flour mixture. Blend in walnuts.
Fill cupcake papers 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until done.
Use toothpick to check doneness.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Mix in heavy 2-quart saucepan, sugar, milk and corn syrup. Cook, stirring constantly over medium heat to a boil.
Boil and stir 2 minutes more.
Take off heat.
Stir in until completely melted chocolate pieces and add peanuts.
Drop with 2 teaspoons on wax paper.
Chill until set.
Makes 24.

title: goulash with noodles
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter or margarine in a saucepan.
Add onions, pepper and garlic; simmer slowly until onions turn yellow. Add chopped beef; continue to cook, stirring constantly, until meat loses its red color.
Break up meat as much as possible with mixing spoon.
Add the paprika and the flour, mixing well.
Add one 8 ounce can tomato sauce and 1 cup water.
Add the bouillon cube, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and the oregano; simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Let bubbling subside.
Add the sour cream, stirring well.
Do not cook after sour cream has been added, or it will curdle.

title: portuguese kale soup
directions: Heat a large saucepan (4-quart minimum).
Add sausage; brown over high heat.
Pour off any fat rendered.
Add olive oil, garlic and potatoes; stir to coat for 1 minute.
Add tomatoes, carrots, chicken stock, bay leaves and thyme.
Simmer, uncovered, until potatoes are tender.
Remove the bay leaves.
Add the kale, pushing it down into the soup.
Cover; simmer until the kale is just cooked.
Adjust seasonings.
Serves 8.

title: roman holiday
directions: Fry onion and hamburg in little olive oil with salt and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.
Make layers of spaghetti and meat in casserole; pour in tomatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover dish. May be frozen now or bake 35 minutes at 350°; remove cover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: chicken and yellow rice
directions: Fry chicken in oil with onion and garlic.
When done, add tomatoes and water.
Boil for five minutes.
Add bay leaf, salt, rice, yellow rice seasoning and green pepper.
Stir thoroughly and place in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Garnish with green peas and pimiento.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, peanut butter and vanilla. Sift flour and soda together and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Roll into balls and press with fork.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Combine remaining ingredients and blend into dry ingredients, without overmixing. Drop by tablespoons into preheated 375° vegetable shortening.
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Place on paper lined baking sheet in warm oven until all are cooked.
Serve with maple syrup. Makes about 12 (2-inch) fritters.

title: egg-asparagus-mushroom casserole
directions: Melt butter; add flour and blend well.
Combine mustard with soup and add to flour mixture. Cook slowly, stirring constantly until thick.

title: french dressing
directions: Shake all together and store in a quart jar.

title: company chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts and cut up.
Combine chicken, soup, mushrooms, pimento and evaporated milk and put into 1-quart greased casserole.
Top with potato sticks.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes, until bubbly.
Enjoy.

title: dilled green beans
directions: Pack beans, lengthwise, into 4 hot sterilized pint jars, leaving 1/4-inch headroom.
Tuck in pimento slices.
Add 1/4 teaspoon mustard seed, 1 clove garlic and dill in each jar.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Trim all visible fat from pork loin and cut into thin strips. Heat oil in skillet and brown the meat strips.
Remove meat and set aside.
Drain the pineapple and combine pineapple juice with water, vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch and soy sauce.
Shake in a glass jar until well mixed.
Cook sweet and sour sauce in skillet until clear and slightly thickened.
Add the meat and cook over low heat for about 1 hour.
About 5 minutes before serving, add the green pepper, onion slices and pineapple chunks.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: french raisin pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients and cook at 425° for 10 minutes in an unbaked pie shell.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake until done.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots for 10 minutes.
Pour over this the celery seed, mustard seed, sugar, vinegar, water and oil.
Cook the carrots, onion, celery and bell pepper until a little tender.

title: judy's oven stew
directions: Place ingredients in a large oven pot with a cover in the order listed above (meat on bottom).
Cover pot tightly.
Place in a 250° oven for 5 hours.
Serve with hot biscuits or hot bread.
Great winter meal!

title: string bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple torte
directions: Combine
flour,
baking soda, salt and cinnamon and set aside. Beat
eggs.
Add
sugar, oil and extract and mix well. Add the flour mixture and stir in the nuts and raisins.
Spoon batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done (50 minutes
to
1 hour;
insert a toothpick in center and it comes out clean).

title: chocolate mousse pudding
directions: Break Heath candy bars and brownies into small pieces.
Layer one-half brownie pieces into bottom of deep dish, glass bowl.
Add layer of chocolate pudding, a layer of Cool Whip and a layer of broken Heath bars.
Repeat.

title: clam chowder
directions: Add onions
to food processor and pulse 7 to 8 times to finely chop.
Remove from bowl and set aside.
Add carrots and potatoes to	food processor and pulse 7 to 8 times to coarsely chop.
Melt butter
in	a
4-quart pot over medium heat.
Add onions and saute until
tender.
Add
carrots,
potatoes
and water.
Cook until vegetables	are
tender,
about
to
20 minutes.
Stir in clams
with juice.	Combine butter and flour to make a smooth paste.
Slowly
add
flour	mixture
to pot, stirring constantly. Add
milk, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat and cook until
soup thickens, stirring constantly.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients, blending well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: manhattan clam chowder, 1947
directions: Heat large pan, add salt pork and render a little of the fat. Put in onion and leek and cook over moderate heat until browned. Add potatoes, tomatoes, celery, green pepper, bay leaf, thyme, water and the clam liquor.
Season.
Bring to a boil over moderate heat; reduce and simmer 30 to 35 minutes, until vegetables are tender.
Cut clams into small bits and drop in soup.
Add caraway seed and cook soup 5 more minutes over low.

title: german potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and serve.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Beat salad dressing, cake mix, eggs, water and cinnamon at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Stir in carrots and walnuts.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Spread frosting.

title: green chile salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Break up canned tomatoes into small pieces.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
(May be refrigerated 1 week.
Store in jar with lid.)

title: shaw's salsa
directions: Mince every ingredient very, very fine.
Then add salt and vinegar to taste.

title: tamale loaf
directions: Mix well and cook about 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Don't let it cook dry.

title: lisa's pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees. Grease a 9X13-inch casserole dish. Place pork chops in dish. Salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle each chop with onion powder, drizzle olive oil over chops. Spread golden mushroom soup over seasoned pork chops. Add chopped onions and carrots. Sprinkle lightly with salt. Place pats of butter on top. Cover with foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours. Turn oven up to 350 degrees, uncover and bake additional 30 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches with 1/4 cup sugar and let stand for 30 minutes. Melt butter in 2-quart baking dish.
Make batter of remaining ingredients.
Pour batter over butter in dish, then pour fruit and juice over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until browned.

title: best scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray or butter large casserole dish. Place layer of potatoes in dish. Crush crackers and layer over potatoes (the more crackers used, the thicker the sauce will be). Sprinkle with salt and pepper; dot with butter and sprinkle with chopped onions or cheese if using. Repeat layers at least 2 times, ending with crackers. Pour warm milk over all and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until fork-tender. If it starts to brown too
much, cover with lid or foil.

title: tuna fish salad
directions: Mix everything together and chill.
Serve over lettuce with other vegetables.
Serves 4.
Has 98 calories, 1 fat gram, food exchanges equals 1 1/2 meat, 1 fat and 1/4 fruit.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix ingredients with slightly beaten eggs.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts; bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool (may then be frozen until needed).
Warm slightly before serving.

title: honey butter
directions: Blend the butter and honey until smooth.
Refrigerate and use as directed.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dreamsicle pops
directions: Mix equal parts of orange juice and yogurt.
Add vanilla extract and sugar to taste.
Pour into popsicle molds and freeze.

title: mountain cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, milk and melted oleo together.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with pie filling (cherry is best).
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375° or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Can be topped with ice cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix with mixer; roll into ball, then roll in chopped pecans.

title: parmesan potato sticks
directions: Peel potatoes and cut lengthwise into quarters.
Cut each quarter into 3 strips.
Roll potatoes in melted butter, then in the mixture of the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broc-stuffing strata
directions: Beat eggs.
Add nutmeg, broccoli, milk, 1 1/2 cups cheese and stuffing.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate (glass).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and return to oven until cheese has melted.

title: strawberry cream nut bread
directions: Blend cream cheese, 1/2 cup white sugar and 1 egg.
In a large bowl, combine flour, remaining sugar, brown sugar, soda, salt, cinnamon and nuts.
Mix eggs and berries and add to dry mix of ingredients just until moistened.
Spread 1 cup batter in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Top with cream cheese mixture, then cover with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool ten minutes and then remove from pan.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar with apples and let stand until sugar is dissolved. Add egg and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir into apple mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into 8-inch square baking pan and bake in 375° oven for about 40 minutes or until done.
Immediately cover with hot sauce.

title: baked ziti
directions: Mix the ziti, cottage cheese, Mozzarella, egg, salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cups sauce together.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, spread 1/2 cup sauce on bottom, then add ziti mixture.
Spread well and top with remaining 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 375° or until sauce is bubbly and top lightly browned.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate decadence
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a nine-inch spring-form pan.
Melt chocolate over low heat or in microwave.
Add beaten eggs slowly to melted chocolate, beating until thickened.
Melt butter with sugar and coffee over low heat.
Whisk in chocolate-egg mixture until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool on counter.
Remove from pan.
Slice and serve with a dollop of whipped cream.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Dice onion; drain string beans.
Mix onion, beans, can of soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 can of fried onions.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Drain and rinse beans.
Mix ingredients.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°, lower to 350° for 15 minutes.
May be served hot or cold. May cook in slow cooker.

title: meat boats
directions: Cut slice from top of rolls and hollow out center of each roll.
Reserve crumbs for meat mix.
Season softened butter with garlic salt lightly and spread on inside walls of rolls.
Saute green pepper and onion in butter.
Soften crumbs in tomato soup and egg.
Mix sauteed onion and green pepper with crumb mixture; add salt and pepper.
Add meat to these ingredients; mix well. Fill hollowed rolls with meat mixture.
Place meat boats on buttered pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in a large bowl. Beat egg, milk and vegetable oil. Add this to flour mixture. Stir in nuts.
Fill greased pans half full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: veach's baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and half the onion; drain.
Add beans and stir.
Add brown sugar, ketchup, mustard and remaining onion. Cook 20 to 30 minutes on medium heat.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Add dry pudding to Cool Whip.
Add pineapple to pudding. Stir with spoon keep refrigerated until ready to eat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown pepper, onion and celery until change in color; add sausage and cook until done.
Drain off grease.
Cook rice and soup in boiling water for 7 minutes.
Mix in sausage.
Pour in casserole dish.
Cover; cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover for last 10 minutes of cooking time.

title: oreo milk shakes
directions: Coarsely chop 14 cookies.
In electric blender, blend chopped cookies, 1 pint of ice cream, milk, and chocolate syrup until well blended and smooth, about 1-2 minutes.

title: tortilla espanola("spanish omelet")
directions: Heat 1/4 cup oil in skillet.
Add potato and onion.
Cook until soft.
Add egg.
When it's almost done, flip onto a plate.
Add 1 tablespoon oil to pan, slide omelet back in and cook until done.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Blend lemon, onion and mayo.
Add celery, almonds and pimento.
Add chicken and toss lightly.
Add salt and pepper. Pour into buttered casserole.
Mix cheese with crushed chips and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Chop the onion, garlic and celery.
Cook in oil until tender. Set aside.
Boil the lentils, split peas and barley.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add onion, garlic and celery.
Add tomato sauce.
Mix vegetables and seasonings.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add macaroni and cabbage.
Cook until tender.

title: chocolate-coated party cake
directions: Mix and bake cupcakes in paper-lined muffin cups as directed on the package of cake mix.
Cool and remove cakes from paper liners. Cut a thin slice from the bottom of each cupcake and carefully hollow-out the cake.
Fill with 2 teaspoons whipped topping and replace cake slice.

title: pot pie
directions: Roll out like pie dough and cut into squares.
Drop into hot broth for 15 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes and oranges
directions: Cut the oranges in half. Remove pulp. Cut fine and set aside. Mash the potatoes.
Add orange pulp and 3 tablespoons oleo, salt and cinnamon. Mix well. Spoon in the 6 orange halves. Sprinkle with the brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Delicious.

title: potato-bacon-corn chowder
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, cook bacon until brown.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Add potatoes, water and seasoning.
Continue cooking 15 to 20 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Reduce heat to low and add remaining ingredients.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until heated through.

title: chocolate nut banana bread
directions: Mix baking powder, flour, soda, salt and sugar in large bowl. Then add butter, eggs, milk, vanilla and bananas.
Fold in coconut and morsels.
Bake at 350° in a loaf pan for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Knead ingredients together, adding flour gradually until dough no longer sticks to bowl or fingers.
Place ball of dough on ungreased cookie sheet with raised sides.
Pat out dough evenly, fork with holes thoroughly and bake at 275° for 1 hour or until browning starts.
Remove, cut and sugar immediately.

title: never fail corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine the dry ingredients in a bowl. Add egg.
Stir in the oil and milk mixture until it is thoroughly mixed.
Spray the bottom of skillet or cake pan with Pam (no-stick spray).
Pour batter in the skillet/pan.
Bake for 20 minutes. Cool 5 minutes and flip the bread onto your serving dish.

title: apple pie(sour cream espanola valley)
directions: Peel and
core
apples
and slice.
Cook in butter five minutes.
Add
sugar and spices to apples.
Cover and cook for ten minutes.
Place
in
pie
shell and cover with sour cream. Place in pie shell and cover with sour cream.
Sprinkle cheese over the top of the sour cream.
Place pie under oven broiler until cheese melts.
Serve warm.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken and next 4 ingredients in large pot and cover with cold water.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Remove chicken from stock. Separate meat from bone.
Return bones to stock and simmer 1 hour, then strain.

title: mexican escalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients. Spread shallow in 9 x 12-inch greased pan until set in center, approximately 1 hour.

title: tangy chicken
directions: Brown chicken in skillet in butter.
Combine Heinz 57 sauce and water; pour over chicken.
Cover; simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is tender, basting occasionally.
Remove cover the last 10 minutes of cooking.
Skim excess fat from sauce before serving.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs in a bowl and then add 2 cups sugar and 3 teaspoons vanilla.
Add salt, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and flour.
Mix well and then add oil and zucchini.
Put batter in two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° in a preheated oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: all-american bread(from "a diary of bread")
directions: Stir corn meal, brown sugar, oil and boiling water together. Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast, sugar and ginger to 3/4 cup warm water.
Stir this into cooled corn meal mixture.
Add the whole wheat and rye flours.
Stir in enough white flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Turn out on floured surface and knead about 8 minutes until smooth and elastic (or use electric mixer). Place in a greased bowl and let rise until double.
Punch down, turn out on floured surface and divide into 3 parts.
Shape each part into a loaf.
Place in greased loaf pans.
Let rise until almost double.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes (until loaves sound hollow when tapped).
Makes 3 loaves.

title: crescent meat loaf
directions: Brown ground beef; add onion powder.
Drain fat.
Mix gravy mix with water and pour over hamburger mixture.
Let simmer 10 minutes.
Put 1/2 the crescents on bottom of square cake pan. Pour hamburger mixture over crescents.
Sprinkle cheese over hamburger mixture, if desired.
Place remaining crescents on top of hamburger and cheese layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until crescents turn golden brown.
Slice, serve and enjoy!

title: quick quesadillas
directions: Spread cheese and green chilies on 1 tortilla.
Place the other tortilla on top and butter.
Spray skillet with vegetable spray and place butter side down in skillet on medium heat. Butter other tortilla and turn until both sides are brown and cheese is melted.
Slice pizza style and dip in picante sauce. Enjoy!

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain and combine all ingredients except part of cheese.
Put in casserole and top with remaining cheese.
Heat in 350° oven until hot and bubbly.

title: delicious sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes in boiling water until done.
Mash well (may cut in quarters so they will cook faster).
Mix mashed potatoes with remaining ingredients.
Pour in a deep Pyrex dish and bake at 350° until set in middle.

title: popcorn gone nuts
directions: Butter large, shallow pan with sides; put aside.
Combine popcorn and nuts in a large bowl.
Combine margarine, sugar and corn syrup in 2-quart saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil and cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Quickly pour syrup mixture over popcorn; gently stir to coat evenly.
Spread in buttered pan to cool.
Cool completely. Break into bite-sized pieces.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add ice cream.
Pour in large square pan.
Allow to stand 1/2 hour in refrigerator.
Mix in pineapple and nuts (reserving 2 teaspoons nuts for top) and stir well.
Top with remaining nuts.
Refrigerate to jell.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat eggs
and	stir
in sugar and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder and add to egg mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Mix well.

title: great dessert
directions: Mix butter with crushed cookies.
Place in large baking dish and bake for 10 minutes.
After this cools, put on a layer of ice cream, then chocolate sauce.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.
Keep frozen.
It may help to freeze between layers.

title: frozen peanut-butter pie
directions: In small saucepan, heat together 1/4 c. heavy cream, the peanut butter and 1/4 c. confectioners' sugar over medium heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat; let cool to room temperature.

Meanwhile, beat together remaining 2 c. heavy cream and remaining 3/4 c. confectioners' sugar until stiff peaks form. Fold cooled peanut butter mixture into whipped cream along with chopped peanut butter cups.
Spoon into prepared crust.
Top with peanut butter cup halves.
Freeze until semi-frozen, about 3 hours.
Cut into 12 slices and serve.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Dice bread into 1/2 inch cubes and saute in hot oil until slightly brown.
Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Shape into balls the size of a large walnut and using a spoon, drop into boiling salted water.
Cover and steam 15 to 20 minutes until dumplings are done through.
Serve immediately.

title: frosting
directions: Add sugar to shortening and beat 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and beat 5 minutes.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Blend together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and pecans.
Mix well and chill. Shape into small balls and place on cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for about 15 minutes. Cool a few minutes before removing from cookie sheet. Roll in 10x sugar.

title: barbecue
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Simmer in covered frying pan over low heat for 30 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over bran flakes and let stand.
In a separate bowl, cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs.
Stir in buttermilk and the bran flake mixture.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda and add to muffin mixture.
Add dates (or raisins), if desired.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: Arrange approximately 45 saltine crackers on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Melt 2 sticks of butter and add 1 cup brown sugar.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a quart jar and shake well.
Keep in fridge.
Shake well before using.

title: bombay chicken with almonds
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet over medium heat; add almonds.
Cook 10 minutes or until almonds are golden brown, stirring frequently.
Sprinkle almonds with 1 teaspoon curry powder; toss lightly to coat.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs and add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add melted butter, leaving the pan buttered. Add chiles and cheese.
Mix together and pour into baking pan.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and vinegar; boil together for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add drained beets to hot sauce and let stand for 30 minutes, more or less.
Reheat carefully and serve.

title: no-guilt chocolate pudding
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and cornstarch in a 6 or 8 cup measure. Gradually stir the milk into dry mixture with wire whisk and cover.
Cook on High for 5 to 8 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring 2 or 3 times.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown the sausage.
Separate dinner rolls into 8 triangles. Place in 12-inch pizza pan with elongated ends to center.
Close in the perforated sides and press dough up the sides of pan.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Remove (will be puffy).
Spoon sausage onto crust.
Sprinkle cheeses.

title: prune bread(from grandmother dora thalmann clasen, circa 1940)
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time.
Mix well after each.
Carefully add sour cream and vanilla, mix until smooth and well blended.
Add dry ingredients and prunes. Mix well.
Pour into buttered loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Measure oats in bowl and set aside.
Combine in pan, sugar, milk, cocoa and oleo.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1/2 minute only.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir well until smooth and pour over oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine cheese, margarine, sugar and extract until well blended.
Add flour; mix well.
Chill overnight.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: nana's chicken divan
directions: Lightly butter bottom of casserole dish.
Boil broccoli spears and layer in dish.
Boil 5 chicken breasts.
Shred meat and layer over broccoli.
Spread cream of chicken soup over broccoli. Spread cream of mushroom soup next.
Mix mayonnaise with lemon juice and spread over soups.
Take cheese, grate it and sprinkle over ingredients.
Sprinkle bread crumbs lightly on top.
Melt butter and pour on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: nannar's tortellini soup
directions: Brown the Italian sausage (taken from casing) and the onion. Add the beef broth, diced tomato and tomato juice; cook for 45 minutes. Cook the tortellini for about 7 minutes. Cook the carrots in microwave until half done. Add the cooked tortellini, carrots and the zucchini to the soup. Cook until the zucchini is tender.

title: old fashioned tea cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll on floured board or cloth to 1/4-inch thick.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: english toffee
directions: Melt butter and sugar in saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture turns caramel colored (usually about 15 to 20 minutes).
Sugar and butter will combine, separate, then combine again.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes after mixture combines for 2nd time.
Pour immediately onto greased metal cookie sheet.
Tilt pan until mixture spreads evenly.
Sprinkle chocolate over top evenly. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Let cool and break into bite size pieces.

title: frosted coffee bars
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream butter, then add beaten eggs and brown sugar.
Alternately add hot coffee and dry ingredients.
Mix in chocolate bits and nuts.

title: german style spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti until barely done.
Heat butter or margarine in large skillet.
Add onion and knockwurst and saute approximately 10 minutes.
Stir in soup, beer, sour cream, horseradish, mustard and caraway seed.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drain spaghetti and place half in greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Spoon over 1/2 knockwurst/soup mixture.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered.
Serves 6.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs.
Beat just until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly in crisscross pattern with tines of fork.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes or until set and just beginning to brown.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet before removing to cooling racks.
Yield: 6 dozen cookies.

title: cheesy bits
directions: Mix shredded cheese and margarine.
Add flour and mix well. Add crisp cereal and mix well. Shape into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten each ball with a fork and bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Spread ground beef in bottom of casserole.
Layer rest of ingredients as they are listed.
Cook at 350° for an hour or until potatoes are brown, uncovered.

title: 3 quick and easy fruit desserts
directions: Mix in a blender until smooth.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill at least 8 hours before serving.

title: celery flavored pickles
directions: Soak cukes, onions and celery in ice water for 2 hours. Drain.
Pack in pint or quart jars.
Combine mustard seed, vinegar, salt, sugar and water.
Bring this liquid to boil and pour over cukes in jars.
Add lids and rings.
Place jars in a boiling water bath for 10 to 15 minutes.
The jars should seal.

title: split pea soup
directions: Wash peas. Add cold water, vegetables and ham bone and simmer for 3 hours or until mixture is thick.
Remove ham bone.
Force peas through coarse sieve and season to taste.
If needed, dilute with milk.
Serve very hot with toasted croutons.

title: icebox coconut cake
directions: Combine sugar, coconut (save some for topping on cake icing), sour cream and whipped topping.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, make cake in 2 layers.
Cool and split; frost with filling.
I heat 3/4 cup milk and a little sugar to sweeten and pour over each layer before frosting.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding & milk. Beat 2 minutes on low. Blend in Cool Whip. Butter bottom of 9x13 pan. Line pan with layer of graham crackers. Pour half of pudding over grahams, top with another layer of grahams & rest of the pudding. Top with third layer of grahams. Refrigerate for 2 hours. After 2 hours, add topping.

title: barbecued ribs(sweet, not hot)
directions: Combine all ingredients except ribs in a 9 x 13 baking dish. Mix thoroughly, then put ribs in mixture and turn until coated. Bake in 350° oven about 2 1/2 hours, turning every 45 minutes.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Stir hot, but do not boil. Put in jars and seal.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and mix with chicken.
Add mushroom soup.
Place in greased casserole. Grate cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done. Cook broccoli as package states. Combine cream of chicken and chicken and rice soups with mayonnaise. Pour soup mixture into buttered casserole dish.

Add layer of shredded chicken. Add layer of chopped broccoli. Top with Stove Top stuffing (prepared by box directions). Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Top with grated cheese and place in oven until cheese melts.

title: streusel-topped pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. With mixer or wire whisk, beat pumpkin, sweetened condensed milk, egg, 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt. Pour into crust. Bake 15 minutes.

title: aunt margaret's potato salad dressing
directions: Boil for a few minutes.
Use this sauce or dressing for wilted lettuce also.

title: graham cracker delight
directions: Mix each box of Jell-O separately with one can of applesauce. Place layer of graham crackers in an oblong baking dish or pan. Cover with Jell-O, another layer of graham crackers then the opposite color of Jell-O.
Do this until all Jell-O is used, then top with Dream Whip.
Sprinkle coconut on top, if desired.
(Tastes like old fashion Stack Cake.)

title: garlic-herb steak marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in a glass measure.
Pour in a sterilized decorative bottle or jar.
Cap and refrigerate.

title: pioneer hall cheese dip
directions: Heat half and half with chili powder, stirring to blend.
Let simmer for few minutes.
Add salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Put cheese in bowl.
Gradually add the hot liquid.
Stir until cheeses are mixed up good.

title: hot cakes
directions: Sift flour, measure; add soda, salt and sugar; sift again.

title: basic muffin mix
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Beat well for 5 minutes until light and fluffy.
Add the baking powder to flour.

Mix baking soda and yogurt and when it foams up, add half of it to the creamed mixture along with half the flour. Blend well, then add the rest of the yogurt and the flour mixtures. It will be very thick.
Place in 12-muffin tin and bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mercer's fudge
directions: Put margarine, sugar and milk into a pan and heat mixture until it comes to a boil. Boil for 8 minutes (230°), stirring constantly. In a large mixing bowl, put chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme and then pour hot mixture over this. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and pinch of salt, if desired. Stir until creamy. Add pecans and drop in small pieces on wax paper.

title: beef and rice casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions slightly.
Add remaining ingredients. Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Butter Bundt pan.
Line with raisins and nuts.
Arrange frozen rolls in pan.
Pour mixture of dry pudding, brown sugar and cinnamon over rolls, then pour melted butter over everything. Cover with a towel and let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Flip out right away.

title: gloria levy's marinated shrimp
directions: One to 4 days prior to serving, prepare the marinade and marinate the shrimp.

title: dishpan cookies(large batch)
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
In a smaller bowl, mix sugars, cooking oil, vanilla and eggs together.
Pour egg mixture over dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Drop on a cookie sheet. Bake until cookies are brown, 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: picnic some-mores
directions: You will need a long handled fork or stick.

title: unknown name - pineapple cake
directions: Bake according to package directions on 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Over medium heat, combine flour, brown sugar, egg, vinegar and pineapple.
Cook until thickened.
Cool.
Fold in Cool Whip, apples and peanuts.
Chill overnight.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to liquid to measure 3 cups.

In a large saucepan, partially cook the bacon. Stir in celery and onion. Cook until celery and onion are tender. Stir in liquid mixture, undrained tomatoes, potatoes, carrots, thyme, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 30 to 35 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Mash slightly to thicken. Stir in clams; heat through.
Serves 4.

title: lemon salad
directions: Heat pineapple; stir in Jell-O.
Set aside to cool.
Fold in buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in large doubled brown paper bag.
Combine sugar, syrup, butter and salt in bowl.
Microwave on High 2 minutes, stir.
Microwave 3 minutes, stir after each minute.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Stir.
Pour over popcorn in bag.
Shake well.
Microwave 1 minute.
Repeat.
Shake well.
Microwave 30 seconds.
Add peanuts, if desired.
Repeat.
Pour on foil or waxed paper to cool.
Store in tight container.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Add all other ingredients except pecans. Mix well with hands.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Shape into ball and roll in pecans.
Keep in refrigerator until serving time.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: chicken breasts piquant
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish, except chicken. Arrange chicken in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until done.
Serve with wild rice.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, milk, margarine and vanilla in saucepan. Let boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal and cocoa.
Spoon onto waxed paper.

title: kahlua torte
directions: Mix pudding with milk and 1/4 to 3/4 cup Kahlua.
Set aside. In a 9 x 13-inch pan or decorative dish, layer the following: cake, Kahlua/pudding, whipped cream and ground Heath bars or toffee chips.
Serves one.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Over medium heat, heat syrup and sugar.
Let it come to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add cornflakes.
Mix until well coated.
Spread into buttered pan. Let cool.
Cut and serve.

title: lemon poke cake
directions: Place cake layers, top sides up in 2 clean 8 or 9-inch round pans.
Pierce cake with large fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Stir boiling water into jello in medium bowl at least 2 minutes until completely dissolved.
Carefully pour 1 c of the jello over 1 cake layer.
Pour remaining jello over second layer.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Dip 1 cake pan in warm water 10 seconds, flip into plate. Spread with about 1 cup of cool whip.
Dip 2nd pan in warm water for 10 seconds.
Carefully place second layer on top of first layer.
Frost top and side of cake with remaining cool whip. Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until ready to serve.

title: quick and easy peanut butter kisses
directions: Combine the above ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Top with a Hershey's Kiss or Brach Star.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove immediately from pan.
Serves 24.

title: volunteers' buttermilk pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Add margarine.
Beat slightly with rotary beater.
Fold in eggs and buttermilk. Beat with a spoon. Add vanilla and pour in crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: bob's chili con carne
directions: Saute onions, garlic and peppers in oil until tender.
Add meat and brown slightly. Add beans, tomatoes and seasonings. Cook slowly 1 hour.
Add a little water while cooking.
Serves 10.

title: lil's artichoke balls
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Make about 1 teaspoon size balls out of the mixture.
Roll the balls in the bread crumbs.
These may be frozen at this point.
If frozen, thaw before baking.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: green tomato sweet relish
directions: Mix tomatoes, peppers, onions and salt.
Let stand one hour. Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients. Tie spices in cloth. Bring to boil.
Simmer 20 minutes or until very hot.
Dip off all juice.
Pack into hot jars and seal.

title: sugar-free holiday jello dessert
directions: Bring 2 cups of water to a boil.
Mix with Jell-O in medium bowl.
Add cream cheese.
Stir until melted.
Now, whisk with a hand whisk until mixture looks foamy.
Drain fruit cocktail, saving juice.
Slowly stir juice and cold water to equal 2 cups. Add fruit and stir in slowly.
Chill until set.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then add flour, salt, soda and sour cream last.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil scrubbed potatoes until fork tender. Take out of water to drain and cool. Mix
onions, lemon juice, dry mustard, black pepper, paprika, salt, dill pickle juice, and Italian salad dressing.
Mix together and stir well then cover, set aside to fluff dry onions.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put all in slow cooker on low for about 6 hours or until meat is tender.
Cut vegetables up as you want them.
Some like thin sliced others like them thicker.

title: melt in your mouth muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat egg slightly.
Add milk and butter to egg.
Mix together with dry ingredients.
Fill greased and floured muffin cups about halfway and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: moist coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix by directions on box.
Add coconut and coconut flavoring; bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix, in a 2-cup measuring cup, the milk, powdered sugar, vanilla and 1 teaspoon coconut flavoring. Fill cup to 2 cups with water.

title: ester berrier's apple nut cake
directions: Mix together oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Cream well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in apples, raisins and nuts. Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: layer lettuce salad
directions: Layer in order in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Spread mayonnaise over the top and sprinkle with cheese.
Refrigerate 2 to 4 hours or overnight.
Stir before serving.

title: mint tea
directions: Combine mint and boiling water in a teapot. Let stand for 10 minutes. Pour into teacups. Add honey.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: my mom's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; simmer about 20 minutes.
Great for barbecued chicken and whatever requires a barbecue sauce.

title: prune cake and glaze
directions: Mix sugar and soda.
Melt margarine.
Add butter and milk slowly.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Pour over cake while hot.

title: chicken breast deluxe
directions: Dip breasts in egg.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Roll up chicken breasts and secure with a toothpick.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken in pan.
Bake, covered, for 20 minutes at 350°.
Turn each roll.
Bake 20 more minutes, covered.
Turn each piece of chicken.
Spoon spaghetti sauce over chicken.
Bake 20 minutes, uncovered.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Scald and peel tomatoes; mash them up and drain off most of the water.
Grind up peppers and onions.
Mix all ingredients and cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Seal in hot canning jars.

title: plantation shrimp pilau
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; save to use later.
Add bacon grease to water in which rice will be cooked.
In frying pan melt butter; add celery and chopped bell pepper.
Cook a few minutes; add shrimp, sprinkled with Worcestershire sauce and dredged in flour. Stir and simmer until shrimp are cooked.
Season with salt and pepper; add rice and mix.
More butter may be added.
Stir in crumbled bacon and serve.

title: rice krispie treats with gumdrops
directions: Heat marshmallows and butter over low heat, stirring constantly
until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla, cinnamon and cereal.
Add gumdrops.
Press in buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cool and cut into bars (2 x 1-inch).

title: peach delight
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with cake mix and press lightly into bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Drain peaches and pour over cake. Beat sour cream and egg yolks together.
Pour over peaches.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix egg white and milk.
Combine remaining ingredients, except chicken breasts.
Dip chicken in egg mixture; coat with cheese mixture.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: mountain bar cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and peanut butter.
Bring to boil for one minute.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop from tablespoon on waxed paper to cool.
Do not flatten.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt oleo and mix with peanut butter.
Put sugar in it.
Roll in little balls and chill it.
Melt the chocolate chips and paraffin together and dip or roll balls in it.

title: mother's forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar.
When stiff, fold in coloring, extract and chocolate chips, if desired.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet using upward turn of spoon to create peaks.
Place in preheated oven and turn oven off immediately.
Leave in oven overnight. Makes 40 to 45 small cookies.

title: oat and banana and nuts cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In large bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and baking soda.
Add eggs, shortening and 1/2 mashed bananas.
Beat 2 minutes or until creamy.
Then add remaining bananas, oats and nuts.
Stir well.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat
egg yolks, sugar and flour together.
Add pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Mix together and cook until thick. Cool. Before serving, add Cool Whip.

title: microwave vegetable casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, combine frozen beans and onion. Pour 1/4 cup water over top, cover and microwave for 14 to 16 minutes until tender-crisp.
Stir once during cooking.
Drain well and combine remaining ingredients except the onion rings. Microwave for another 15 minutes, stirring and turning once during cooking.
When cook time remaining hits the 2 minute mark, top casserole with the French fried onion rings.

title: microwave pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt together, mix in milk. Microwave 7 to 10 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add meat, garlic and onion.
Stir over medium-high heat until meat is browned.
Add hot pepper sauce, chili powder, barbecue sauce, tomatoes, salt, cumin and kidney beans; mix well.
Cover and simmer for an hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: applesauce
directions: Quarter and remove stems from apples.
Do not peel. Place in a large pan.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook until it comes to a boil, then simmer until apples are cooked. Mash with a potato masher while cooking.
Once completely cooked and mashed, put through food mill.
Jar and refrigerate.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix salt and sugar and sprinkle over top.
Boil sugar, syrup and water until it cracks in water.
Add peanuts, let it boil up, then add soda and let boil up again.
Line buttered pan with peanuts and pour mixture over.

title: olive-filled cheese balls
directions: Cream cheese and butter thoroughly.
Stir in flour and cayenne until blended.
Pack one teaspoon of cheese mixture around each olive, covering completely.
Place balls on greased cookie sheet. Bake in hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes.
Makes about 25 balls. Serve hot.

title: cranberry-strawberry salad
directions: Heat pineapple, cranberry sauce, strawberries and 3/4 cup water to nearly boiling point.
Dissolve both gelatins in remaining 1/2 cup water.
Add dissolved gelatins to fruit mixture. Mix well.
Pour into long baking dish.
May add nuts if desired. Serves 12 to 16.
A must with turkey and dressing.

title: busy day soup
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add hamburger (raw and broken up); boil for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate dream pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together; let cool for 10 minutes. Mix topping into chocolate (not chocolate into topping). Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate for 2 hours. Cut small pieces because it is a very rich pie.

title: western meal in one
directions: Brown beef in oil with garlic.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until onion is transparent.
Drain off fat.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine spinach, artichokes, cream, salt, pepper and 1/3 Parmesan.
In a small bowl, with mixer at medium, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Reduce speed to low, gradually add milk, mixing until just well blended.
Spoon spinach mixture into shallow 1 1/2 qt. casserole 8x8.
Pour cream cheese mixture evenly over spinach mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/3 c. Parmesan.
Bake for 25-30 minutes until bubbly.

title: potato skins
directions: Scrub potatoes and prick with fork.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 425° or microwave on High power.
Cut potato in half and scoop out inside, leaving 1/2-inch thickness of potato.
Save potato insides for other use, if desired.
Combine cooking oil, chili powder and hot sauce to taste, if desired.
Brush inside of potatoes with mixture and cut potatoes in half again lengthwise. Space potatoes on baking sheet and sprinkle with bacon, tomato and onion.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes, until cheese is melted and potato quarters are heated. Serve warm with sour cream.
Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese may be used as topping instead of veggies, if desired.
Heat 5 minutes.

title: cheesy potato bake(microwave)
directions: Line two 1-quart casserole dishes with plastic wrap.
In large bowl, stir soup until smooth.
Stir in Vegetable Base and succotash until blended.
Add potato nuggets; toss to coat. Divide mixture among lined casseroles.
Fold plastic wrap over mixture; seal tightly.
Cover with lid and freeze until firm.
Pop frozen potato mixture out of dish.
Overwrap with foil; seal with freezer tape.
Return to freezer.
To heat one frozen casserole, peel off all wrapping.
Place potato mixture in 1-quart casserole dish.
Cover with lid; microwave on High 5 minutes.
Rotate casserole.
Reduce power to 50%.
Microwave 15 minutes or until hot, stirring gently once during heating.

title: round raisin bread
directions: Combine raisins, water and soda.
Bring to a boil.
When mixture begins to foam, remove from heat and cool.
Beat together eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add the raisin mixture alternately with flour to the egg mixture.
Pour batter into 4 well-greased and floured cans.
Bake a little over an hour at 350°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cocktail franks
directions: In medium saucepan, cook franks in boiling water for two minutes.
Drain and place in dish.
In small saucepan, combine chili sauce, sweet pickle relish, water, mustard and celery seed. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until hot and well blended.
Pour over franks.
Keep warm and serve on toothpicks.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Fry sausage first.
Scramble eggs.
Boil dirty rice.
When sausage and eggs are done, mix together in rice mixture, then add diced celery and diced olives.

title: eggnog
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Whip until fluffy.
Pour in glasses; sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together.
Add walnuts, salad oil, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together cinnamon, soda, flour and salt; add to mixture.
Bake at 350° until sides of cake leave the pan.
Top with Cool Whip when serving.

title: breakfast-brunch egg casserole
directions: Cut bread into squares and place in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer sausage, then cheese over bread crumbs.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over layers in dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and cream again.
Sift flour and soda; add alternately with milk, blend in mashed bananas and nuts.
Use 6 bananas, if they are small.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic.
Drain grease.
In a large pan, combine hamburger mix, tomato sauce and paste.
Add water. Add rest of the ingredients and simmer on low heat for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Combine corn, sour cream, eggs and salad oil.
Beat well. Combine corn meal and baking powder.
Add to corn mixture.
Pour into greased 10-inch iron skillet.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: orange hazelnut tea bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Spread hazelnuts onto baking sheet and place in preheating oven until lightly toasted and fragrant (about 5 to 8 minutes).
Remove from oven and immediately rub hazelnuts in a clean, dry tea towel to remove skins.
Finely chop 3/4 of nuts and coarsely chop remaining nuts.

title: raisin rocks
directions: Sift flour once; measure. Add baking soda, salt and spices. Sift together 3 times. Work butter with spoon until creamy. Add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy. Add egg. Beat well. Add flour alternately with combined milk and molasses, a small amount at a time, beating until smooth after each addition. Add raisins and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake in hot oven (400°) for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 3 dozen Rocks.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion, then add peppers.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt.
Simmer while dividing biscuits.
Divide 5 biscuits to line an 8 or 9-inch pan.
Combine 1 cup cheese, sour cream and egg.
Mix well with meat.
Spoon over dough and place remaining biscuits on top.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes until biscuits are brown on top.

title: moussaka (greek)
directions: Saute in oil separately until done the onion, eggplant and hamburger.
Drain; set aside.
Salt to taste.
Make a sauce with 3 tablespoons oil and the flour.
Cook over low heat.
Add the stock and milk; cook until thickened.
Add a little to the egg yolks, then put the egg yolks in sauce.
On a buttered casserole dish, layer eggplant, meat, cheese, sauce and nutmeg.
Repeat layers. Beat egg whites; smear on top.
Sprinkle a little cheese and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: turkey indienne
directions: Saute green pepper in margarine. Blend in flour, curry powder, onion soup and water. Cook slowly until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add turkey, mushrooms and almonds.
Simmer 10 minutes. Good served over rice.

title: french meat pie
directions: Shape each loaf of bread dough into a ball; cover and let rise according to package directions until nearly doubled. Punch dough down; cover and let rise 10 minutes.

title: baked catfish with peppers and tomatoes
directions: Sprinkle fish with lemon juice and allow to stand about 15 minutes.
Dredge with flour and fry in oil.
Place the fried fish in a baking dish and cover.
Saute onion, green pepper and hot pepper until softened.
Add tomatoes and wine, cook another 3 to 4 minutes.
Place the sauteed vegetables on the fish and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: gumbo
directions: Cook bacon.
Remove and drain.
Measure 3 tablespoons bacon fat in skillet.
Add onion and saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender. Put in dish and crumble bacon on it.

title: grandma fulton's whiskey balls
directions: Mix vanilla wafers, nuts, and cocoa together.
Add corn syrup and whisky and stir together.
Roll into small balls and then roll in powdered sugar.
chill for about 12 hours.
(I usually also chill the mix before I roll them into balls as this makes it a little less like playing with mud pies)

title: wassail
directions: Heat all ingredients until mixture comes to boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix and sprinkle coconut and pecans in 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Mix cake according to directions and pour over coconut and pecans.
Do not stir.
Combine powdered sugar, softened cream cheese and vanilla.
Drop cream cheese mixture by spoonfuls all over top of cake batter.
Do not stir.
Bake according to mix directions.
Serve by the spoonful.
Top of cake looks like an earthquake.

title: watermelon-green peppercorn salsa
directions: Cover the red onion with cold water and let stand 10 minutes to remove some of the acidity.
Drain and pat dry with paper towels.
Remove the rind from the watermelon and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Remove as many of the seeds as possible.
Combine with red onion, 2 tablespoons lime juice, the green peppercorn, salt and cayenne.
Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Just before serving, stir in the remaining tablespoon lime juice.

title: dill green tomato pickles
directions: Use small, firm green tomatoes.
Pack into sterilized jars. Add to each quart jar a clove of garlic, 1 rib celery and 1 green pepper, cut in fourths.

title: sour cream meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs, 1/2 cup sour cream and milk.
Stir in bread crumbs, onion, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt and pepper. Add beef; mix.
Bake, uncovered, in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: chicken nacho bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place chips in a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Mix refried beans, 1 cup cheese and salsa until blended; spread evenly over chips.
Mix chicken and seasoning; sprinkle over bean mixture.
Top with remaining cheese and onion.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Top with tomato.
Serves 4.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.
Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut. Heat oleo and cream cheese until soft enough to stir in 10x sugar. Spoon into cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not cut until cold.

title: grandma's irish soda bread
directions: Mix in large bowl (by hand) flour, sugar, salt, baking soda, baking powder and raisins.
In another bowl, mix eggs and buttermilk.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients and mix well.
Grease 2 medium size loaf pans and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lee's strawberry cake
directions: Fold strawberries into pudding and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: lasagna
directions: Cover flat casserole with 1 cup sauce.
Place 1 layer uncooked lasagna on top of sauce.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups of sauce, crumbled tofu and spinach in that order.
Dribble 1 cup Melty Cheese over layer.
Repeat layers 2 more times, total of 3 layers.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves and butter melts.
Let cool slightly.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt to mixture, stirring well.
Pour filling into shell; top with pecan halves.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: california blend veggies
directions: Parboil vegetables and drain.
Melt butter, add flour and milk; cook until smooth.
Blend in cream cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Combine with vegetables, put in cake pan or casserole dish and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake covered for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover, top with bread crumbs and bake 30 more minutes.

title: kids garbage
directions: Melt butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Pour over Chex, raisins and peanuts.
Put it in a clean garbage bag with powdered sugar, 1/2 box or more.
Shake well.
Can be refrigerated.

title: bristo chicken
directions: Stir salad dressing and seasonings.
Place chicken on grill or broiler pan.
Brush chicken with half of sauce.
Grill or boil 8 to 10 minutes; turn and brush with remaining sauce.
Continue to cook 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Preparation time:
5 minutes.
Cooking time:
20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: lo-cal carrot-raisin-nut salad
directions: Combine and chill.
Makes four servings, approximately 150 calories each.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat onion, celery and pepper in microwave until tender.
Add Cheez Whiz and pimento.
Break up frozen broccoli; add to cheese mixture.
Add cooked rice.
Cook at 350° until bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: peanut butter sundae cake
directions: In ungreased 9-inch pan, stir together first 4 ingredients. Mix in next 3 ingredients.
Mix with a fork until smooth.
Stir in peanut butter.
Spread evenly in the pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Pour 1 3/4 cups hot tap water over the batter.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Serve over favorite ice cream.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Brown beef and set aside.
In a large saucepan, put milk in and heat on medium-low.
Cut up Velveeta cheese.
Add to milk and let it melt.
Add chili, sauce and tomatoes.
Stir and mix well. Add hamburger.
Stir in Mexican cheese.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook to soft ball stage sugar, evaporated milk, butter and salt.
Add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: double corn muffins
directions: Mix all together until lumps are out.
Spoon into large greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Each muffin is 146 calories, 4 gm. protein and 6 gm. fat.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and chill several hours.
Use with fresh vegetables.

title: peach delight salad
directions: Dissolve
gelatin in hot
water.
Chill
to
egg
white consistency.
Beat with electric
beater
at
high speed until double in quantity.
Add softened
cream cheese which has been previously	mixed with whipped
topping.
Beat
until
smooth. Add peaches and beat at low speed
for 1 minute.
Pour in mold and chill thoroughly.
When congealed, unmold and garnish with lettuce and peach slices.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix in.
Roll dough in small balls in sugar.
Place about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Microwave chocolate, milk and margarine in medium bowl on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir unti chocolate is completely melted.
Spread evenly in crust. Refrigerate 30 minutes or until chocolate is firm.
Arrange banana slices over chocolate.
Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spoon over bananas in crust.
Spread with whipped topping.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.

title: chili
directions: Cut up onion and
brown in butter.
Add hamburger; stir and cook until no longer red.
Add tomato juice and salt.
Cook slowly, about 1/2 hour.
Add kidney beans.
Break up and add spaghetti.
Cook slowly until soft.
Add water, if necessary.
Add chili powder last.
Allow about 1 hour or longer to make, stirring occasionally.
Can be reheated or can be frozen for later use.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Make according to directions on box.
Bake 325° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until done.
This is for 3 layers.

title: grammies' white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup of warm water and set aside.

title: baptist pie
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges well.
Put in bowl with lemon juice, Eagle Brand and Cool Whip.
Beat until smooth; place in pie crust.
Chill well several hours.
You may garnish top with nuts and maraschino cherries, if you desire.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients but ginger ale.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
A small amount can be frozen with cherries and floated in punch bowl.
This will help keep punch cold.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Mix gelatine, brown sugar, salt and spices thoroughly in saucepan.
Stir in milk, water, egg yolks and pumpkin.

Mix well. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until gelatin is dissolved and mixture is heated thoroughly, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat and chill, stirring occasionally until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.
Beat eggs whites until stiff; beat in sugar.
Fold gelatine mixture into stiffly beaten whites.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Serve topped with whipped cream.
(Oh, so good!)

title: chili
directions: Mix beans and tomatoes and put on low heat.
Brown bacon and mix with beans.
Brown chopped onions in bacon grease.
Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Mix browned ground beef, onions and chopped garlic to the bean mixture.
Cook slowly for 2 hours.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Pour in 7-Up and the rest of the ingredients.
Leave set until cool.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown onion, green pepper and celery; add ground beef.
Cook until done.
Add tomato soup; cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Pour into baking dish and top with favorite pie crust.
Bake at 350° until crust is done.

title: hush puppies
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water; add egg and milk.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop in hot oil and fry until brown.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in tightly covered container.
For each serving use heaping teaspoon per cup of boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and add liquid ingredients and pour
in
an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: boiled dressing
directions: This dressing can be kept covered in refrigerator for a few days.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: sourdough beef dip
directions: Mix well all ingredients (blender) except bread.
Slice top off bread round and hollow out carefully, making sure there are no weak places in bread shell. Fill bread shell with beef mixture and put top back on.
Wrap in foil and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Use soft bread from interior of loaf (plus more if needed) to dip in hot mixture.

title: dancing snowballs(for kitchen chemists; not for consumption)
directions: Use a very large, clear, glass bowl.
A big brandy snifter, round flower bowl and a narrow, tall vase work very well.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and put in 9 x 13 inch pan. Melt butter, mixing in flour and milk; pour over chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until top is brown.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Mix together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Combine the eggs, oil and milk and stir into the dry ingredients until just moistened.
Stir the berries into the batter and spoon into medium-size muffin tins lined with cupcake liners until about half full.
Bake 20 minutes. Yield:
2 dozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Add sugar to softened cream cheese.
Stir in milk and peanut butter.
Fold in whipped topping and pour into shells.
Top with the other carton of whipped topping.
Sprinkle with crushed peanuts.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix 7-Up and spaghetti sauce together.
Pour over chicken. Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Cover with foil the last 1/2 hour of baking.

title: tomato soup to can
directions: Cook tomatoes, onions, celery and parsley together until soft. Also cook the bay leaves and cloves in this mixture.
Strain. Mix flour, sugar, salt and pepper with 2 cups water to form a paste.
Add flour paste to tomato mixture.
Bring to a boil and add butter.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, salt and soda and add alternately with buttermilk and flavorings.
Mix well pour into greased and floured tube pan until cake tests done at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut eggplant in chunks.
Boil until tender; drain. Mash with butter.
Add slightly beaten egg, onion, grated cheese, milk and seasoning.
Mix well and bake 30 or 40 minutes at 350°.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients ahead of time and refrigerate until ready to use.
Add ginger ale or 7-Up just before serving.
Serves 20. I usually freeze some of mixture in a mold to put into punch and keep it cold while serving.

title: coconut oatmeal crispies
directions: Mix together.
Shape into long rolls and wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate or freeze until firm.
Cut in 1/4 inch slices. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix ingredients together and sprinkle over batter before baking.

title: german style pickled carrots
directions: Scrape and slice carrots.
Cook in boiling water until tender; drain.
Add onion, salt, sugar, oil, vinegar and water.
Mix and let marinate a while before serving.

title: chili
directions: In a skillet, saute onion and garlic. Set aside.
Brown ground beef and drain.
In a crock-pot, mix tomato sauce, tomato paste, kidney beans, sauteed onion and garlic.
Add beef and bay leaf to mixture. Add spices.
(Additional chili powder and pepper can be added to suit your own taste.)
Cook on high for 30 minutes; turn to low setting and cook slowly for several hours, stirring occasionally.
This will be a fairly thick chili.

title: shrimp salad in croissants
directions: Place shrimp and water in 12-cup casserole.
Cover and microwave 4 minutes.
Remove and let stand 2 minutes.
Drain shrimp and cool under cold water; drain, shell and devein.

title: spoon bread
directions: Stir corn meal into 2 cups of milk.
Heat mixture to a boil, stirring constantly, until it makes a mush.
Add rest of milk and eggs.
Stir in salt, baking powder and melted butter.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: double peanut candy
directions: Grease a small cookie sheet or square cake pan.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter in saucepan.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Pour onto cookie sheet or into cake pan.
Chill. Cut into squares.

title: crab boil
directions: Put all in pot.
Cover with water.
Boil until potatoes are tender.

title: glorified chicken
directions: In a 12 x 8-inch baking dish, arrange chicken skin side up. Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Spoon soup over chicken.
Bake 20 minutes more until chicken is tender.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate overnight.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Heat water and beans to boiling in Dutch oven.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Add enough water to cover beans if necessary.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: one dish hot dish
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Brown meat with onion and salt and pepper.
Drain.
In large casserole dish, combine all ingredients. Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for one hour.
Serve with salad and rolls.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Melt together margarine and marshmallows.
Add crushed graham crackers.
Stir in all other ingredients and mix well with hands. Pack in a cake tin or any container that can be sealed and stored in refrigerator.
I add cherry juice if too thick.

title: banana rhubarb crisp
directions: In
a medium bowl combine bananas, rhubarb and 2 tablespoons sugar,
cinnamon and nutmeg.
Spoon the mixture into a well greased
shallow baking dish.
In a medium bowl, combine the flour,
graham
cracker
crumbs and baking powder. With a pastry blender,
cut
in
butter
until
mixture
is crumbly. Combine egg
and
milk and stir in.
Spoon batter evenly over fruit. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar over top of batter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.
Serve with ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: brownies and cream
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Line two 8 x 8-inch baking pans with waxed paper.

Combine butter and chocolate in a large microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on High, stirring frequently, until chocolate is melted, about 1 1/4 minutes. Stir to mix well. Add sugar, flour and vanilla extract to chocolate mixture; mix well. Let stand to cool slightly. Add eggs and mix well. Spoon mixture into the prepared baking pans.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil over medium heat; boil 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop on wax paper and chill.

title: marinated sliced tomatoes
directions: In a cup or small bowl, combine all the dressing ingredients. Stir with a wire whisk until blended.
Arrange the tomatoes on a platter or in a bowl.
Pour the dressing over the tomatoes.
Cover with plastic wrap and put in refrigerator at least 1 hour to blend flavors together.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes and add butter, sour cream and cream cheese. Blend well.
Place in a casserole dish and bake 45 minutes at 325°.
You can add cheese and paprika.

title: sensational spinach side dish
directions: In a large frying pan, place oil and chopped spinach over medium heat.
Combine eggs, cheese, milk, salt and pepper in a separate bowl.
Then pour egg mixture over the spinach in pan. Gently stir occasionally, until eggs are cooked.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, pudding, butter and eggs until light and fluffy. Stir in dry mixture. Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding mix.
Then add Cool Whip, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix the day before using.
Stir before serving.

title: lemon lush
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and chopped nuts.
Mix well and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Blend cream cheese and powdered sugar together until smooth.
Fold in half of Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.

title: flowerpot dirt cake
directions: Combine margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
In another bowl, combine pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Combine both of these fillings.
Crush in a Ziploc bag the Oreos.
Layer in pot the cookies and filling.
You should wind up with cookies on top for soil.
Cover and freeze 5 to 6 hours.
Take out at serving time and add silk flowers or greenery and gummy worms.

title: lemon fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Prepare pudding mix as directed on box.
Add juice from 1/2 lemon; cool.
Whip cream and fold into pudding. Add drained fruit; mix well.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and onion until done, but not browned.
Mix all together and bake in casserole at 400° about 45 minutes.
Thirty minutes is enough for me.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix Bisquick, sugar, milk and butter.
Add peaches.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar before baking. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon pie
directions: Stir and let cool for 10 minutes and add pure lemon juice or rind of lemon.
Stir and put in one 9-inch pie shell.

title: chocolate raspberry vanilla cream bars
directions: Heat oven to 350. Grease 15x10x1 inch baking pan. In a large bowl, combine cake mix, 1/3 c. butter, and egg. Mix until crumbly. Press in bottom of greased pan. Bake at 350 for 8 to 12 minutes or until crust puffs and appears dry. Cool 5 minutes. Spread preserves over base. Cool 25 minutes or until completely cooled.

title: chicken dinner in foil
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Line 18 x 15-inch dish with aluminum foil (heavy-duty).
Lay the chicken first, then carrots and potatoes all around the chicken.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Coat mini tins with graham cracker crumbs (rub soft margarine and sprinkle with crumbs).

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix flour, sugar and egg in small bowl.
Mix until fine.
Put pie filling in baking dish, 9 x 9-inch.
Sprinkle mixture of flour, sugar and egg on top of pie filling.
Chip up a stick of margarine on top.
Cook in oven at 350° until brown.
You can also use cherry pie filling.

title: italian salad
directions: Wash and cut broccoli.
Lay in bottom of bowl; then cut, wash and break apart cauliflower.
Lay on broccoli.
Then on top put washed and sliced cherry tomatoes.
Then pour dressing on.

title: squash bake
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper; drain well.
Add raw squash and 1 cup water.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add rice, soup, salt and the other cup of water.
Stir well and pour into a 9 x 9-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 with 250 calories and 6 grams fat.

title: hot dogs in a bun
directions: Roll up two hot dogs in a paper towel.
Put the rolled up hot dogs in the microwave.
Cook for 1 1/2 minutes.
Caution:
The hot dogs are hot!
Serve in a bun (mustard and onions optional).

title: green beans with walnuts
directions: Steam beans until tender. Mince garlic. Heat olive oil in skillet and saut garlic, beans and walnuts until everything is warm (approximately 2 to 3 minutes). Serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: cherry moos(mennonite recipe)
directions: Bring cherries, juice and water to boiling.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add enough sweet cream to make a smooth sauce.
When the cherries come to a boil, pour in thickening and stir until the mixture comes to a boil again.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch cast-iron pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook stew in a 15 to 20-gallon kettle, stirring constantly while cooking.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In large bowl, mix together all veggies.
In small bowl, blend sour cream, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing together.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.

title: butterhorns
directions: Combine 2 1/2 cups flour and yeast.
Heat milk, sugar, shortening and salt until warm (115° to 120°), stirring constantly until shortening almost melts.
Add to dry mixture; add eggs. Beat at low speed for 1/2 minute.
Beat at high speed for 3 minutes.
By hand, stir in 2 to 2 1/4 cups flour.
Knead for 5 to 8 minutes, until smooth and elastic.
Put in a greased bowl to rise.
Cover; let rise until double (about 2 1/4 hours).
Punch down.
Divide in thirds.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Roll into a 12-inch circle.
Brush with butter or margarine.
Cut in 12 wedges and roll into crescent shape.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, margarine, milk and salt to soft-ball stage. Add the marshmallows and peanut butter just before removing from stove. Do not stir. Let cool slightly. Add vanilla and beat until creamy and holds shape when dropped from spoon. Pour into buttered pan.

title: marinated salad
directions: Drain corn, beans, peas and pimientos.
Combine in a large bowl.
Mix oil, salt, vinegar and sugar together.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight; for best results, make 1 day ahead.
Stir mixture every 4 hours.

title: sans soucis trout bretonne
directions: Coat trout with flour, salt and pepper.
