Saute in oil until well browned.
Place on ovenproof platter and heat in 375° oven for 5 minutes or until done.
Saute mushrooms in same skillet after removing excess oil.
Stir in margarine, lemon juice and shrimp; heat through.
Pour over fish and sprinkle with parsley.
(Trout fillets may be substituted for whole trout.
In that instance, omit oven heating step.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and gradually add sugar, then oil.
Combine dry ingredients, add to egg mixture alternately with zucchini.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Turn into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes, then turn out on wire rack to finish cooling.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Heat butter, onion, salt, celery salt, pepper and milk to scalding.
Stir in potato puffs.
Continue cooking until smooth, stirring constantly.
Soup should be consistency of heavy cream. If desired, garnish each serving with paprika and parsley.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, water and peanut butter. Sift flour, soda and salt together; add to creamed mixture.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet by teaspoon or form into small balls. Flatten down with fork dipped in cold water.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine ingredients. Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour. Seems better if frozen awhile.
M-mmm good!

title: slim your slaw
directions: Dressing:
In a small bowl, stir together the yogurt or mayonnaise, dressing mix and honey until blended.
Thin with a little water to make of drizzling consistency, if necessary.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into hot oil and fry until golden brown.

title: fried cucumbers
directions: Dip cucumber slices in eggs; dredge in bread crumbs.
Fry cucumbers in deep hot oil until browned on both sides.
Drain well on paper towels.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Sprinkle Jell-O over cottage cheese; stir.
Add Cool Whip and mandarin oranges.
Mix together, chill and serve.

title: cool rise rapid mix rolls
directions: Combine 2
cups
flour,
undissolved yeast and sugar in large bowl; stir
well to blend.
Add soft margarine.
Add hot tap water to
ingredients
in
bowl
all
at
once.
Beat with electric mixer at
medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add 1 cup more flour.
Beat with electric mixer at high speed for 1 minute or until
thick and
elastic.
Stir in remaining flour gradually with wooden spoon.
Use just enough flour to make a soft dough which
leaves sides
of
bowl.
Turn
out onto floured board. Round up into a ball.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes or until dough is smooth
and elastic.
Cover
with plastic wrap, then a towel. Let
rest
for 15 to 20 minutes on board.
Punch down.
Shape into
pan
rolls as desired.
Brush surface of dough with oil. Cover
pan
loosely with
plastic
wrap.
Refrigerate 2 to 48 hours.
Uncover;
let stand
mintues.
Preheat
the oven. Puncture
any
surface bubbles
with
an oiled toothpick just before
baking.
Bake
for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan.
Brush with margarine.
Cool on rack.

title: frozen strawberry cheese pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and sour cream.
Reserve 1/2 cup berries and syrup.
Mix remaining berries and syrup into cheese mixture. Pour filling into baked pie shell.
Cover; freeze until firm.

title: caramel pie
directions: Tear labels off cans.
place in boiling water for 3 1/2 hours. Make sure the cans stay covered in water.
remove cans with tongs because they will be very hot.
Open, pour into pie crust. refrigerate for 2 hours.
Put Cool Whip on top, then add pecans and chocolate chips on top if desired.
Enjoy!

title: quick and easy broccoli chicken
directions: Saute rice vermicelli mix with margarine in a large skillet on medium heat until golden brown.
Add 2 cups water, special seasonings and basil.
Bring to a boil on high heat.
Place chicken on rice.
Cover; reduce heat to low.
Simmer 10 minutes. Stir broccoli and tomato.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes or until rice is tender and chicken is no longer pink inside.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; let stand 3 minutes.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Blend all except last 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Cook mixture over medium heat.
Stir constantly until it bubbles.
Cool in cold water until thick.
Beat egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar until stiff. Fold into pumpkin mix.
Pour into crust and chill.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast and water in large bowl. Add sugar, salt, egg and half of flour. Mix well. Add shortening and mix well. Add rest of flour in small amounts. Mixture will be very stiff. Let rise until double. Knead and set rolls to rise or makes 2 loaves.

title: heaven and earth
directions: About 1 hour before serving, cook the potatoes in 1 cup boiling water with salt in a large covered saucepan.
Stir in apples and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until apples are tender-crisp.

title: fudge cake
directions: Bring butter, cocoa and water to boil.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Stir.
Do Not Beat!
Add buttermilk, mixed with soda, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 350 degrees until cake tests done.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in baking pan.
Stuff with dressing.
Seal with a toothpick.
Mix soup and bouillon cube and water.
Pour over pork chops.
Cover with Reynolds Wrap.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°, then uncover for 15 or 20 minutes to brown.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, shortening and sugar until light and creamy.
Add eggs one at a time; beat until creamy.
Mix flour and baking powder together and add alternately with milk.
Add flavorings, but not at the same time (add these one at a time all during the mixing of the mix).
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Preheat oven to 325° and bake for 2 hours or 1 hour and 50 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl combine first 5 ingredients until well blended. Stir in chopped pecans.
Pour in pie crust.
Bake at 350° in oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: apricot cake
directions: Blend sugar, oil and eggs.
Combine flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to oil mixture alternately with baby food apricots. Fold in pecans.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours (start in cold oven) at 325°.
While cake is warm, drizzle Apricot Glaze on it.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut into wedges.
Cook until tender in unsalted water.
Peel and chop onion.
Rinse red pepper; remove seeds and membranes.
Cut into strips.
In a skillet, saute ground beef in 1 tablespoon of butter until it loses its pinkness.
Add onion, red pepper and garlic.
Season to taste with a dash of pepper and salt.
Add vinegar, parsley and crumbled bay leaf. Cook for a few minutes.
Transfer mixture to a lightly greased casserole.
Drain potatoes.
Mash quickly.
Add remaining butter, spices and half and half.
Beat until mixture is light and fluffy. Spread mashed potatoes over meat mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until pie is hot and potatoes are lightly browned.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar, and shortening together. Add eggs and blend together. Stir in molasses. Sift remaining ingredients together and add to first mix. Roll dough into small balls. Roll in sugar. Space balls 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet. DO NOT PRESS DOWN COOKIES. Bake at 350 degree for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and chopped onion in boiling salted water for 5 minutes. Drain and combine with chicken soup, sour cream and shredded carrots. Combine stuffing mix and oleo. Spread 1/2 of stuffing mix over 12 x 7 1/2 x 2 casserole. Spoon vegetable mix over stuffing. Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over vegetables. Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: raisin walnut deluxe pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl with mixer on low speed, beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, butter or margarine and vanilla. Beat until well blended.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool completely on wire rack before cutting.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco and add sugar.
Add vanilla, flour and crushed potato chips.
Butter cookie tins and drop teaspoon size dough.
Bake in 325° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 72 cookies.

title: shephard pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; salt.
Blend in gravy mix and water.
Add basil and vegetables.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Fold cheese into potatoes. Spoon in ring on top of casserole.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° for about 40 minutes until set.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Thaw Cool Whip.
Mix chocolate pudding; mix with Cool Whip. Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 pudding mix evenly, then graham crackers, then pudding mix.
Line graham crackers on top.
Let cool.
Spread icing on top.

title: raisin puff cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water until water is absorbed.
Set aside to cool.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Beat until fluffy. Stir in flour, soda and salt.
Add raisins and vanilla.
Mix well and shape into small balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.
This is a soft cookie.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: baby food plum cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, apples, sugar, pecans and eggs in a large bowl. In separate bowl, sift flour, soda and salt.
Add this to apple mixture.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Bake in 3 layers at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef steak ranchero
directions: Cook beef in salt, pepper, tenderizer, and corn oil until beef is brown.
Add tomato juice and water.
Cover and simmer until beef is tender; add jalapenos and onions.
Cook for about 2 more minutes.
Serve with corn tortillas.

title: olive-rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in tightly covered casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.
Rice will absorb the moisture.
If recipe is doubled, add 15 minutes cooking time.
Serves 6.

title: s. o. s.
directions: Brown ground beef until it crumbles and is very brown.
Remove all juices.
Add onion and continue browning, then add garlic. Add pepper and salt.
Mix 1/2 cup flour and 1 cup milk together and pour in meat mixture.
Add milk and water to make it the thickness you desire.
Add the margarine and stir until it is melted.
Serve over toast.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add milk alternately with flour mixture, adding grated lemon rind during mixing.
Put into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When done and while still hot, pour juice of one lemon with 1/4 cup sugar over bread.
Allow to cool.

title: pistachio bundt cake
directions: Place ingredients in mixer bowl and mix at low speed for 1 minute and at higher speed for 3 minutes.
Pour 2/3 of batter into well greased Bundt pan.
Add to the remaining 1/3 of batter, 3/4 cup Hershey's chocolate syrup.
When well mixed, pour over the batter in the pan.
Run a knife through the batter to marbleize it.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check after 45 minutes.
Allow to cool in pan 10 minutes before putting on plate.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Combine all ingredients together and put in refrigerator at least 24 hours before using.
This is equivalent to one can of Eagle Brand milk and much cheaper.
I use this repeatedly.

title: company potatoes
directions: Wash, peel and cook potatoes until soft.
Cream potatoes with electric mixer until smooth and add sour cream, cream cheese and margarine.
Mix until smooth.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.
The depth of the casserole dish may cause a variance in the baking time.
This recipe may be made days ahead of time and refrigerated.

title: hot tamales
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients in a food processor.
Pour over ground beef and corn meal.
Mix well and shape into the size of link sausage.
Roll in meal mixture made with meal, salt, pepper and cumin.
Put on coffee filter.
Sprinkle about 1 1/2 teaspoons meal mixture over tamale.
Roll tightly in filters.
Pack tightly in a large pot with a rack in the bottom.
Place tamales open side down.
Weigh down with a plate.
Pour into pot the remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.
Remove from broth; drain well. Allow time for tamales to firm up before serving.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to package directions, cool.
Punch holes in brownies with fork and pour Kahlua over brownies; set aside.
Whip up chocolate mousse according to package directions.
Break Skor or Heath bars into small pieces.
Break up half the brownies and place in bottom of a glass trifle dish.
Cover with 1/2 of the mousse, layer with 1/2 the candy bar pieces, then 1/2 the whipped topping. Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Instead of alcohol, may substitute 1 tsp. sugar and 4 Tbsp. leftover black coffee.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Mix in other ingredients and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Uncover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: pie crust
directions: Dump all in bowl and mix.
Can use dough hook to start mixture, then finish with spoon or your hands.
Can be divided, made into a ball, wrapped in wax paper and frozen for future use.
Will make 4 single pie crusts.

title: onion-mushroom roast
directions: Line baking pan with 2 sheets of aluminum foil, crisscrossing them in pan.
Place roast in center of pan on foil.
Place mushroom soup on top of roast and 1/2 to 1 full package of dry onion soup.
Seal up both pieces of foil tightly.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 2 1/2 to 4 hours.
No basting necessary.
Juices from meat makes its own gravy.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Combine
cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar, divide in half and set aside.
Cream together butter and 2 cups sugar until light and fluffy.
Add
eggs,
one
at
a
time, beating after each. Sift together
flour,
baking
powder
and
baking soda.
Add sifted ingredients to creamed mixture, little at a time.
Add sour cream; mix well.	Add vanilla.
Fold in chopped nuts and raisins and pour
in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Swivel half of the
sugar
and cinnamon
mixture through batter and sprinkle other half
on
top. Bake
in preheated 375° oven for 50 minutes.

title: party pizza bites
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Measure biscuit mix into mixing bowl. Add all other ingredients.
Mix the biscuit mix into the other ingredients with the pastry blender until well blended.
Shape mixture with teaspoon into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 1-inch apart.
Place in oven; bake for about 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: hot potato soup
directions: Put potatoes and onions in pot with chicken broth.
Season and bring to a boil.
Turn to low, partially cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Place mixture in small batches in blender and puree.
Put back in pot and add butter and cream.
Heat thoroughly but do not boil.
Garnish with chives.

title: jiffy rice pudding
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture boils and thickens.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: angel drops
directions: Beat whites and sugar until peaks form.
Add salt and vanilla, then fold in nuts (pecans work best).
Drop by a spoon onto a foil lined cookie sheet.
Place into a preheated oven, then turn off (350°).
Let stand in oven overnight.
If not completely dried, preheat oven again.
Stores well.

title: apricot jello mold
directions: Heat 2 cups nectar; add one pkg. of jello.
Put into mold and chill.
When jelled spread sour cream over jello.
Then heat 1 3/4 cup of apricot juice; add other box of jello and baby food.
When it begins to set pour over sour cream, allow it to jell completely.

title: pickled hot peppers
directions: Wash and core hot peppers, leaving seeds in.
Slice in food processor.
Heat vinegar.
Let peppers stand in vinegar for about 3 minutes, then drain vinegar.
Put peppers in another kettle, then add oil, garlic cloves and oregano.
Mix and put in hot jars.

title: banana delight
directions: Combine 1/2 stick oleo and graham crackers; spread in pan. Combine next 3 ingredients and beat with electric mixer no less than 15 minutes.
Spread this over crumbs.
Layer remaining ingredients in the order given.
This is better when left in the refrigerator overnight.

title: diet cheese cake
directions: Put a graham cracker in bottom of 4 individual dishes.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over crackers.
Makes 4 servings.
Each counts as 1 milk exchange, 1/2 bread or 50 optional calories.

title: dad whitehead's beef gravy
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Simmer 15 minutes. Thicken.
Add barbecue sauce and pinch of red pepper.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add 1 egg at a time and beat well. Add flour, nuts and fruit. Pour into a greased pan and put in preheated oven at 375°. After cooking 15 minutes, take out and stir mixture. Do this 3 times. When mixture is stirred the third time, pack into cake pans and cook 15 minutes longer. Take out and cake is ready. Let cool.

title: chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken in pot on stove until cooked.
Reserve 3 to 4 cups stock.
Debone and store chicken in refrigerator.
Put potatoes in crock-pot, top with carrots, onions, mixed vegetables, seasonings and top with soup.
After 2 hours, add 3 to 4 cups chicken stock. Mix. Let cook until potatoes and carrots are tender, approximately 8 hours.
About 1 hour before serving, add cut up chicken.
Yields about 4 cups.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make cake mix according to directions on box.
After you take it out of oven, prick with a fork.
Pour Kahlua over cake and let cake set overnight.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef.
Add whole tomatoes, water and tomato sauce.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer until almost thick.
Cook enough lasagna noodles (approximately 8) to make 2 layers.
Place in flat glass baking dish (9 x 13 x 2-inch) in this order:
layer of noodles, layer of sauce, thin layer of cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat.
Bake 30 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well with fork.
Add shortening; mix until crumbly.
In small bowl, beat together with fork, water, vinegar and egg.
Combine the two mixtures, stirring with fork until all ingredients are moist. Divide dough into 5 portions.
Chill 1/2 hour.

title: rosalynn carter's strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease a 10-inch angel food pan or 10-inch Bundt pan.
Combine cake mix, strawberry gelatin, vegetable oil, nuts, eggs, flour and strawberries in a large bowl. Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Pour batter into pan and bake 55 to 60 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes. Turn out of pan to cool completely. Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until soft.
Layer 1/2 of potatoes in bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with half of soup.
Then cover with half of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes, until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Add meat and
brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add
soup and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat through.
Serve with noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apricot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes before turning pan upside down.
Frost while hot with powdered sugar diluted with lemon juice.

title: sweet and sour meatballs(yields 25 servings)
directions: Drain pineapple tidbits, reserving syrup.
Set pineapple aside. Add water to reserved syrup to make 1/4 cup liquid.
Combine syrup mixture, can of cranberry sauce, bottled barbecue sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour over meatballs.
Bring to boiling.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Blend 1/4 cup cold water into 1 tablespoon of cornstarch.
Stir into skillet.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add pineapple and 1/2 cup green pepper strips.
Simmer covered until green pepper is barely tender.
Serve as appetizers or may be served over hot cooked rice.

title: chewy chocolate chip raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray cookie sheets with nonstick cooking spray.
In large mixing bowl, with electric mixer, beat together the first 7 ingredients.
Stir together the flour, baking soda and salt; beat into creamed mixture.
Stir in bran flakes, chips and raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove immediately to cooling racks.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil, eggs and sour cream for batter.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Put 1/2 batter in greased and floured 13 x
9-inch cake pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 of the brown sugar mix. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: uncle john's graduation pesto dip
directions: Pesto:
Puree the basil leaves, garlic, pine nuts and olive oil.
Then add Parmesan cheese, Romano cheese and salt and pepper. Whirl until blended.

title: basil dinner rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine 6 c. of flour, sugar, salt and yeast. Add water; beat until smooth. Add enough remaining flour to form a soft dough. Turn onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 8-10 minutes. Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Punch dough down; knead several times. Cover and let rest for 10 minutes. Meanwhile, combine the basil, walnuts and cheese; reserve 2 Tbsp. for topping. Shape dough into 32 balls. On a floured surface, roll each ball into a 4 inch circle; place about 1 1/2 to 2 tsp. of basil mixture in the center of each. Pinch dough together over filling. Place 16 rolls each, seam side down, on two greased baking sheets with rolls touching. Cover and let rise until doubled, about 45 minutes. Brush tops with butter; sprinkle with reserved basil mixture. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve warm.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix salad dressing, sugar and vinegar in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: chili-dog casserole
directions: Fix Hamburger Helper as directed on package.
Add chili and hot dogs, cut in 1-inch slices; mix well.
Put in baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Put slices of cheese on top.
Add Tater Tots.
Bake in oven at 350° until Tater Tots are done.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Place coconut and pecans in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam. Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed on box and pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix and drizzle cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar over unbaked cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: banana pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Pour into 9-inch tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Check after 1 hour as ovens may vary.

title: cheese blintzes
directions: Trim crusts
from
bread and roll flat.
Beat the cream cheese, vanilla, 2 tablespoons sugar and egg yolk together and spread
on	the
bread
slices.
Roll
up each slice.
Roll in melted margarine, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Freeze unbaked. Cut into
3 or 4 slices before baking at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve warm. Also good cold.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, water chestnuts, onions, mayonnaise and cheese. Put in buttered casserole dish. Top with crushed Ritz crackers, mixed with butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: longhorn cheese salad
directions: Combine jello, water and sugar.
Add pineapple with juice and cream cheese.
Cool for a few minutes, then add Longhorn cheese and nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: butter gooey cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Mix in confectioners sugar, eggs and pecan pieces.
Press on top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cake is done when crust and top are golden brown.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a saucepan.
Let simmer about 1 hour.
Then add raw ground beef in small pinches and cook 30 minutes more.

title: fuzzy punch
directions: Soften sherbet and mix with pineapple juice.
Pour Sprite or ginger ale slowly over mixture to make a foam.
Dip spoonfuls of vanilla ice cream over top of punch after it's in the punch bowl. Serves about 50.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Chop cucumbers into fine pieces (almost pulp; do not put in blender).
Cream into cheese with remainder of ingredients.

title: cheese filled jumbo shells
directions: Cook shells according to directions (15 minutes).
Drain and cool in single layer on waxed paper.
Combine 3 cheeses, eggs, parsley, oregano and salt and pepper (to taste).
Fill each shell (2 tablespoons).
Spread thin layer of sauce on bottom of 9-inch square or 8 1/2 x 11-inch oblong pan.
Place shells, open side down, in single layer in pan. Cover with remaining sauce.
Lightly grease a sheet of foil and cover the pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or so.

title: fresh strawberry pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Combine water, sugar and cornstarch in pan. Cook over medium heat, stirring all the time until it comes to a boil. Cook 2 minutes longer or until thick. Add strawberry Jell-O. Stir until Jell-O is mixed. Pour cooked mixture over berries in pie shells. Chill until set. Top with Cool Whip.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oatmeal, oleo and boiling water.
Let stand 20 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a 9 x 13 pan.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Press your hamburger meat in bottom of long pan (not cooked). Salt and pepper to taste.
Then add your cream of mushroom and creamy onion soup on top of that.
Put your cheese slices on top of soup.
Then top with Tater Tots (spread evenly across).
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Then uncover and bake 30 more minutes.

title: cheese spread
directions: Melt all of the ingredients and stir until smooth.
Store in covered containers.
Serve with crackers.

title: twinkle, christmas stars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Empty both mix pouches into bowl.
Add egg and lemon peel.
Mix well. Divide dough in half.
Roll out 1/2 about 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured surface. Cut with cookie cutters that have been dipped in flour.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Brush lightly with beaten egg. Decorate with colored sugar, currants or sprinkles or bake plain (no egg wash) to frost later. Repeat with remaining dough.
Bake 6 to 7 minutes.
Cool 1 minute. Remove from cookie sheet with spatula. Makes 36 cookies.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Peel an slice cucumbers.
Let stand overnight in 1/2 cup salt and 3 quarts water.
Drain next morning.

title: banana split pie
directions: Beat first three ingredients for 15 minutes (do not underbeat) with electric mixer in deep dish bowl.
Put mixture in prepared graham cracker crusts; divide evenly.
Top with sliced bananas and drained crushed pineapple.
Cover with lid to graham cracker crusts and refrigerate overnight.

title: maple pecan candy
directions: Liberally grease an 8-inch square pan with butter.
In heavy saucepan, combine maple syrup, cream and butter.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil. Continue cooking for 9 minutes, stirring often.
Remove pan from the heat.
Stir in the pecans and lemon extract.
Stir for 5 minutes.
Pour candy into prepared pan.
When completely cool, cut into squares.

title: garlic chicken wings
directions: Rinse and dry off wings.
Place in bowl with lemon juice, garlic powder and salt and pepper.
Marinate 4 hours.

title: magic fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a baking dish.
Mix milk, sugar, flour and baking powder and pour over butter.
Do not stir.
Pour fruit over batter.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Fruit will sink and batter will rise.
Add a little cinnamon to peaches or apples.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix together.
Put in the ice cream freezer; let crank until solid.
Store in containers in freezer.

title: chicken, cheese and rice casserole
directions: Slice chicken into strips; brown.
Set aside.
Melt butter in a skillet; add rice from both boxes and brown.
In a rectangular casserole pan/dish, combine chicken, rice, contents from both boxes of rice, water (as per directions on rice boxes), tomato sauce and 1 cup cheese.
Cook at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Add remainder of cheese to top and cook 5 additional minutes. Servings:

title: crock-pot casserole
directions: Place layers of vegetables in order given.
Then add hamburger.
Mix tomato soup and water.
Pour into crock-pot.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours.

title: apricot-pineapple salad
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together.
Beat egg and add flour and few spoons juice or water to thin enough for pouring into boiling juices.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and mix 2 tablespoons Cool Whip and pour on top of jello dish and chill.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Bake in 2 large greased loaf pans at 325 for 50 - 60 minutes.

title: chili rellenos squares
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Sprinkle chili's and grated cheese evenly over bottom of square 8-inch baking dish. pour eggs over cheese mixture.
Bake 1 hour or until firm in center.
Cool; cut in squares.
These are great for breakfast.

title: supper salad
directions: Cook Creamettes (any variety) for 10 minutes or until tender. Drain and rinse with cold water.
Combine with all the vegetables.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Melt margarine. Add to mixed dry ingredients. Pull all ingredients to mixer. Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: shoe peg corn
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Cover top of casserole.
Dribble butter over top.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: date pudding
directions: Boil together for a few minutes and pour into a baking dish.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: In large bowl beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Stir in juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill until set.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: steak au poivre
directions: In a heavy-duty sealable plastic bag or between 2 sheets of wax paper, crush peppercorns and fennel seed coarse with bottom of a heavy skillet.
Pat steaks dry and coat both sides with peppercorn mixture.

title: maud's caramel corn
directions: Remove from heat and stir in soda.
Pour over popped corn. Put in a 200°
oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.
You may add peanuts if you wish.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in
salted water.
When soft, rub through strainer.
Scald milk; add
to potatoes.
Melt butter; add dry ingredients.
Stir until
well mixed.
Stir into boiling soup. Cook 1 minute; strain.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: frozen cucumber salad
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion and salt.
Let stand 2 hours. Squeeze out juice; rinse with water and drain.
Mix sugar and vinegar.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Freeze.

title: disgustingly rich brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°, then smear the inside of 8 or 9-inch square baking pan with shortening.
Melt the butter over a low heat.
In your bowl, stir the cocoa and sugar together, then stir in the melted butter, add the eggs and vanilla and stir again.
Now add the flour and salt and mix until smooth (add your nuts if you want).
Pour mixture into pan and spread evenly.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes, or until brownies just begin to pull away from the sides of the pan.
Check with toothpick to see if it is done.
Cool before cutting into squares.

title: orange delight
directions: In large bowl, mix Cool Whip, cottage cheese, Jell-O and drained pineapple.
Blend well; add nuts and stir well.
Cover bowl and chill in refrigerator until cold.
Serve in dessert bowls.

title: amish corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a baking dish.
Melt 1 tablespoon of butter in small skillet over medium heat.
Add scallions and cook for 4 minutes.
In small bowl whisk together flour and 1/2 cup milk until smooth.
In large bowl whisk together eggs, remaining milk and seasonings.
Add milk and flour mixture plus remaining 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Whisk well to combine. Quickly stir in corn and scallions and pour mixture into dish. Bake 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Will jiggle a little, but should not be liquid in center.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, butter and vanilla in saucepan.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened (about 12 minutes).
Add coconut and pecans.
Cook until thick enough to spread, stirring occasionally.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: bread and butter sticks
directions: Cut each slice of bread into 4 sticks.
Combine butter, seasoning, and Parmesan.
Stir well to mix.
Brush on both sides of the sticks.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet and bake at 400 degrees for 5 minutes.
Turn the sticks over and continue baking for another 5 minutes or until the sticks are lightly browned.

title: strawberry pie(danish dessert)
directions: Put berries into pie shell (cut up if very large).
Make Danish dessert according to directions on package.
Cool and pour over the berries.
Top with whipped cream.

title: olive nut spread
directions: Mix cream cheese with mayonnaise.
Stir in chopped pecans, salad olives, olive juice and a dash of pepper.
Mix well. Filling will be slightly mushy, but after a few hours of refrigeration, it will be spreading consistency.
Keeps well refrigerated for a week or two.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In large bowl put flour, sugar and salt.
Bring margarine, water and cocoa to boil. Pour over mixture.
Beat eggs.
Add sour milk, soda, cinnamon, salt and vanilla.
Mix all together and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar and ground cinnamon; set aside.
In a bowl, stir together flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, ground nutmeg and salt.
In another bowl, combine beaten egg, milk and 1/3 cup melted margarine or butter. Add to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened.

title: cranberry checkerboard salad
directions: Heat cranberry sauce in saucepan.
Strain, reserving cranberries.
Mix liquid with 3 cups water in bowl.
Add gelatin, stir until completely dissolved.
Add lemon juice and salt, mix well.
Chill until thick.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups thickened gelatin mixture.
Pour remaining mixture into chilled 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Mix peanuts, marshmallows and sugar together in a large bowl. In a saucepan, heat chips, milk and butter until smooth and melted.
Pour over nut mixture and coat well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Refrigerate until cool. Cut into bars.

title: smores for one
directions: Put marshmallows and chocolate bar between two layers of graham crackers. Eat warm or room temperature.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients, except baking soda and 1/4 cup water.
Mix together baking soda and water, then add to mixture.
Mix well and pour into well-greased loaf pans, about 2/3 full.
You can also use 4 (1 pound) coffee cans for this recipe.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: black and whites(half moons)
directions: Mix margarine and sugar; beat together.
Add rest of ingredients and drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost with 1/2 chocolate frosting and 1/2 white frosting when cool.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 15 x 10 x 1 inch pan.
Mix all ingredients until crumbly.
Press firmly and evenly into pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheesy sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium skillet, fry sausage until done.
Drain on paper towel.
Save 2 tablespoons fat.
Saute onion and green pepper for 2 to 3 minutes.
Slice/chop sausage. Combine cheese and flour.
Stir in sausage slices, green pepper and onion.
Spread in pie crust.
Mix remaining ingredients and put in pie shell.
Bake on cookie sheet 35 to 40 minutes until browned and filling is set.
Serve with cheese grits, blueberry muffins and Orange Julius!

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Defrost and drain spinach well.
Drain artichoke hearts and cut in quarters.
Mix cheese, mayonnaise, chilies, spinach and artichoke heart pieces.
Pour mixture into medium size quiche pan or Pyrex dish.
Place under broiler for several minutes until top is brown.
Serve with crackers or tortilla strips.

title: funny cake
directions: Melt chocolate in the water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in margarine and vanilla.
Set aside.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well and serve with fresh fruit.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: mexican hot sauce
directions: Blend ingredients.
Add onions last.
Put into saucepan and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until sauce thickens, approximately 30 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and water bath for 10 minutes.

title: chicken and spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cut celery, onions and bell peppers. In large skillet, add shortening, celery, bell peppers and onions.
Cook until tender.
Debone chicken.
Add all ingredients; place in large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook yams, drain, add sugar, eggs, vanilla and butter; beat together in mixer.
Put in casserole dish.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat margarine, brown sugar, sugar and egg.
Add vanilla, flour, salt, soda, oats, coconut, raisins and milk.
Mix.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 13 minutes at 350°. Yields 4 to 5 dozen.
Don't overbake.

title: angel cookies
directions: Mix ingredients given.
Form in small balls and dip in cold water, then in white sugar.
Place on a cookie sheet, sugar side up, and bake at 350° for about 9 minutes.

title: healthy and good bread(for breadmaker machines)
directions: Place ingredients in the mixing pan in the order listed.
Set machine for Light-Basic Wheat program (2 hours and 20 minutes). Watch the dough as it mixes.
If it isn't firm enough, add 1 to 2 tablespoons flour as it mixes.
Remove from the pan as soon as the baking cycle is completed.

title: best ever scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix melted butter and salt; add flour to mixture, then add milk.
Add Velveeta cheese.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or in crock-pot on high for 3 1/2 hours.

title: reese's peanut butter squares
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and spoon and press mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips with milk. When melted, spread on top of mixture and refrigerate.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle half of bacon and onion over bottom of crust. Add half of ham and cheese. Repeat layers. Combine eggs, mustard and cream. Pour over layers. Let stand 10 minutes. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, corn syrup, chocolate, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until knife comes out clean. Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients until firm dough.

title: rice pudding
directions: In large nonstick pan, combine rice, milk, butter and 1/8 cup sugar. Bring to a boil; simmer for 1/2 hour. Combine remainder of sugar, vanilla and eggs in a bowl; beat until smooth. Remove rice mixture from heat; add egg mixture and stir well. Place in container to chill. Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Combine with grapes, marshmallows, coconut and walnuts.
Mix sour cream and sugar; stir into fruit mixture.
Chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: snowball peaches
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and preserves until blended.
Stir in pineapple.
Place peaches cut side up on a lettuce lined serving platter; fill with cream cheese mixture. Garnish with mint if desired.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart casserole. Combine celery soup, milk and cream cheese in a saucepan; heat until smooth.

Combine hash brown potatoes, onion and cheese; mix with sauce. Pour all into the buttered casserole. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Remove the foil; sprinkle the top with sharp cheese. Bake for 15 more minutes or until lightly browned.

title: hazel's oven stew
directions: Spread meat in flat pan.
Work tapioca around meat.
Add vegetables, salt and pepper.
Pour juice over all.
Cover tightly. Bake for 5 hours at 275°.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix together; pour into crust.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix together well.
Grease an iron skillet and have it warm. Pour mixture into skillet and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine flour, salt, egg yolks, sugar and milk.
Mix the filling ingredients together and bring to a boil (stir until it thickens).
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour over peanut butter mixture and let cool.

title: blueberry kochen' cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
In a 1 cup measuring cup put egg; add enough milk to fill the cup.
Add this mixture to flour mixture.
Continue to add the cooking oil.
Mix all ingredients thus far with a fork.
Fold in blueberries.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice.
Mix together and pour into crust.

title: ice cream cone pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place almonds on baking sheet and toast, stirring occasionally until lightly browned (10 to 12 minutes). Cool completely.
Crush cones into small pieces using rolling pin and waxed paper.
Place almonds and chopped cones in a medium size bowl.
Stir chocolate chips and butter in small, heavy saucepan over low heat until melted.
Pour over cones, stirring to coat evenly.
Press 1/3 of crumb mixture evenly over bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Spread half of the ice cream over.
Repeat with 2 more layers of crumbs and ice cream, ending with crumbs on top; press down on crumbs with hands to help adhere.
Cover with foil and freeze until firm.
The pie may be frozen up to 1 month, if desired.

title: pumpkin gingersnap pie
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pie filling mix.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute or until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in Cool Whip, pecans, gingersnaps, pumpkin and pumpkin spices.
Spoon mixture into crust.
Freeze 6 hours or overnight or until firm.
Let stand about 20 minutes to soften before serving.
Garnish with a dollop of Cool Whip and sliced strawberries.
Store leftover pie in freezer.

title: fruit salad dip
directions: Using mixer, combine softened cream cheese, marshmallow whip, ginger and honey.
Remove beater.
Using spoon, fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate until serving time.
Serve over assorted fresh fruit.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot oil, cook the chicken until well browned on all sides; stir in tomatoes, wine, garlic, salt, basil and pepper and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add onions and green peppers; cover and simmer 15 minutes or just until vegetables are fork-tender.
In cup, stir cornstarch and water until smooth; gradually stir into chicken mixture and cook, stirring frequently, until chicken is fork-tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mince and stew onion in mushroom soup and juice from peas. Cook together about 10 minutes.
Season with red pepper and Worcestershire sauce; add peas.
Put into baking dish in 2 layers, putting cheese between layers.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs. Bake about 30 minutes in moderate oven.

title: cucumber and onion salad
directions: Cut cucumbers into thin slices; cut onion into thin strips. Combine in serving dish.
Combine sour cream, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper in bowl.
Mix well.
Add to cucumber mixture; mix gently.
Chill until serving time.

title: sauce for pork loin roast
directions: Mix together and pour over roast last half hour of cooking. Baste often.
Makes enough sauce for 3 to 4 pound roast.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook and set aside lasagne noodles.
Simmer sauce with ground meat and set aside.
Lightly beat 4 eggs and add Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Add oregano and salt and pepper. Mix lightly.
Line large rectangular pan with 1/2 the sauce followed by the cheese mixture.
Repeat, omitting the sauce. Cover with remaining sauce and sliced Provolone cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Allow to stand before cutting.

title: party ham sandwich
directions: Soften butter or margarine. Mix poppy seed, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and onion. Slice rolls in half. Spread with butter mixture. Layer with ham and cheese. Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: uncooked fundoughs #1
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Stir in oil and water.
Add more water, as necessary, to form a soft, pliable dough.
This dough keeps well.

title: nacho layered dip
directions: Mix beans and seasoning mix together.
Melt sour cream and layer as listed in an 8 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch casserole dish.
Bake in oven until cheese melts and bubbles.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in the boiling water, then add the cold water and mix.
Combine jello, strawberries and crushed pineapple after adding water to jello.
Pour half the mixture in dish. Chill.
Spread sour cream over mixture.
Add remainder of mixture over jello.
Chill.
Serve when congealed.

title: tadpole-in-a-hole
directions: Blend egg, undrained corn and half of the cheese.
Add muffin mix; stir until the dry ingredients are wet.
Spoon batter into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pat sausage links dry with paper towel. Arrange sausage links on top of the batter.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes or until top is golden.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls to form rectangle.
Pinch together perforations.
Bake according to crescent roll directions.
Cool.

title: apple bread pudding(makes 6 servings)
directions: In a buttered 8 x 8-inch baking pan, layer half the dry bread cubes.
Dot with butter.
Combine eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Pour over bread.
Lightly sprinkle cinnamon over top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: dallas salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
May be served on lettuce, in avocado half, stuffed in a tomato or as a sandwich spread.

title: mint glazed carrots
directions: In a small saucepan, steam carrots over boiling water until just tender-crisp.
Drain.
Heat butter in a deep skillet.
Add carrots, lemon juice and sugar; cook over medium heat, shaking the pan until carrots are coated.
Add chicken broth and continue cooking slowly until liquid is evaporated and carrots are light golden.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add mint and mix in well. Serve immediately.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix in bowl, cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: potato candy
directions: Mix mashed potatoes (nothing added to potatoes, just boil and mash) with powdered sugar and vanilla.
Roll out on wax paper. Spread peanut butter over the mixture and then roll.
Cut into slices about 1/2-inch thick.
Refrigerate.

title: country ham casserole
directions: Heat cheese, milk and mayonnaise together over low heat, stirring until sauce is smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple or peach cobbler
directions: Peel and core fruit and place in baking dish.
Slice each piece of bread into 5 narrow strips and place over fruit.
Mix sugar, milk, flour, and lemon juice.
Stir in margarine.
Add egg and mix well.
Pour over fruit and bread strips.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until fruit is tender.
Serves 6-8.

title: drop sand tarts
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well; add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: noodles
directions: Add a good pinch of salt to eggs.
Add water.
Add flour for a very good stiff dough.
Roll 1/2 of dough at a time.
Flour the board or table top so it does not stick.
Place the rolled sheets very thin, one of them on top of the other with flour between so not to stick together.
Then roll as for a jelly roll.
Slice very thin and shake out so the strings do not touch.
Have your chicken broth, beef or whatever you want boiling.
Add a few at a time and stir so not to stick to bottom of pan.
Do not overcook but be sure they are done, but not mushy.

title: shepard's pie
directions: In a large skillet brown the beef, onion and garlic.
Drain fat.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix and spread in an 8-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden and bubbly.
Serve with a variety of favorite crackers.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Beat eggs with fork.
Add enough flour to make dough stiff but pliable.
Roll out on board and then roll up and slice thin to make noodles.
Drop and stir into boiling chicken broth or soup. Cook about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana boats
directions: Will need tinfoil and a fire.

title: old-fashioned molasses cakes
directions: Mix ingredients and drop by spoonful on cookie sheet and bake at 325°.

title: lemon almond chicken
directions: Combine lemon juice, mustard, garlic and pepper.
Add 5 teaspoons of the oil. Add chicken to the marinade and let sit at least one hour.
In a large skillet, saute almonds in 1/2 teaspoon of oil until brown.
Remove.
Drain chicken; reserve marinade. Cook chicken in remaining oil for 6 to 10 minutes.
Add marinade to pan and add chicken broth and cornstarch mix.
Heat until mixture reduces by half.
Add marmalade.
Melt.
Stir in butter, parsley and red pepper flakes.
Return chicken to pan and add almonds.
Garnish with lemon.
Serve with rice or your favorite side dish.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix 10x sugar with chocolate pudding.
Add each ingredient except milk.
Add milk 1 tablespoon at a time, mixing after.
Keep mixing until blended.
Add another tablespoon of milk, if needed. Line small pan with waxed paper.
Add mixture and pat flat. Refrigerate 1/2 hour, then cut.

title: scripture 47 cake
directions: Follow mixing directions for any basic fruit cake.
Bake slowly in moderate 350° oven.

title: french toast
directions: Mix egg, flour and milk (add milk slowly) to make mixture like pancake batter.
Cut bread diagonal and dip in batter and drop into hot oil (in a Fry Daddy or skillet).
Cook to golden brown and turn and cook other side to golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and add syrup.

title: carbonara
directions: Cook bacon crisp; crumble into bits and set aside.
Drain fat from skillet.
Add butter and onion; cook until soft.
Stir in Prosciutto.
Add chicken broth and bacon.

title: smoky salmon spread
directions: Drain and flake salmon in mixing bowl.
Beat cream cheese with lemon with mixer until blended light and fluffy.
Beat in flaked salmon and green onions until thoroughly combined.
Season with liquid smoke to taste; stir.
Chill several hours before serving to allow flavors to blend.
To serve, spread on crackers or French bread rounds.
Makes 20 servings.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Season chicken breasts.
Brown in 350° oven.
Add sherry and cook for 30 minutes.
Add soup and well drained mushrooms.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes, basting every 15 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and chop.
Saute onions, celery, garlic, mushroom stems, thyme and basil in margarine until soft (about 15 minutes).
Add shrimp, oysters and wine.
Cook until shrimp and oysters are done (about 15 minutes).
Remove from heat and allow to cool.
Add salt, pepper, crab meat, egg, bread crumbs and green onions.
Mix thoroughly.
Put mixture in mushroom caps and bake at 350° until caps are cooked (about 10 minutes).

title: beef and beans
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet.
Put in baking dish.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chewy oatmeal fruit cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs; add vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake 10 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour milk over crumbs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Press gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly.
Store lightly covered.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream together butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in molasses and eggs; add flour and spices.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Dip tops in sugar.
Place 2 1/2-inches apart on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Blend next 6 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° in pie shells for 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Freezes well.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: In a saucepan, over medium-high heat, melt 1/4 cup spread (butter or oleo).
Blend in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until mixture begins to boil and thickens.
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Combine cheese sauce and macaroni in a 2-quart casserole.
Melt remaining butter; stir in cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes or until hot.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa, flour and sugar together.
Be sure all lumps are smoothed
out.
Add 3 cups of water; cook in double boiler until desired thickness.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix
cake
mix	and
vanilla pudding mix together well. Add light
rum,
water,
oil
and
eggs; mix well.
Grease and flour Bundt
pan.
Bake
at 325° for 50 minutes.	When cake is done, have syrup ready to pour on hot cake in pan.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Combine juice and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add margarine and cinnamon and mix well. Stir in apples.
Spoon into 10-inch prepared pie crust.
Top with second crust and seal.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumbers and onions.
Let set 3 hours. Mix together remaining ingredients to make syrup.
Rinse cucumbers, then pour over syrup and store in refrigerator until needed.
(Do not cook syrup.)

title: a #1 cheese ball
directions: Shred cheese while cold, then allow to come to room temperature.
Beat with cream cheese until blended. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Chill. When firm enough to handle, form into a ball and roll in nuts. Best if made 24 hours ahead.
Yields 1 1/4 pound cheese ball.

title: hawaiian fruit salad
directions: Mix together the first 8 ingredients; set aside.
Place the bananas and remaining 3 ingredients in blender on mix setting for just a few seconds, then pour over fruit mixture.
Stir and chill about 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: Heat butter and oil in large skillet and cook onions.
Add chicken pieces and save.
Add broth, cover and simmer 45 minutes. Take chicken out of broth.
Combine flour and sour cream.
Put into the remaining broth mixture.
Heat and stir with a wire whisk until sauce thickens.
Put chicken back in sauce.
Add pimentos, marjoram and pepper to taste.
Serve over noodles.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chips and margarine; cool.
Add marshmallows and nuts. Divide mixture in half to form 2 rolls on which has been sprinkled coconut.
Roll and wrap.
Chill 24 hours and slice.

title: italian hamburgers
directions: Mix hamburger and crumbled, wet bread.
Mix all ingredients and make into patties.
Top with Gray Poupon or Dijon mustard.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into shell.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: mary starts cut-out cookies
directions: Cream egg yolks, oleo and sugar.
Add soda, cold water and flour.
Knead and roll out.
Beat egg whites and brush on top of cookie.
Also may add colored sugar before baking.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 dozen large cookies.

title: great baked chicken(low-fat)
directions: Clean and take skin off thighs.
Put in a large baking pan. Combine marinade.
Pour over chicken.
Refrigerate for 16 hours in marinade.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, uncovered. This is especially good to cook while you're at church if you have a timer on oven.

title: party crab bake
directions: Combine the cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream and onions.
Place a layer of macaroni in bottom of 2-quart greased casserole.
Alternate with cheese mixture and crabmeat (making the top layer crabmeat).
Arrange sliced tomatoes on top.
Sprinkle with salt, then top with sharp Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together in large mixer bowl for 15 minutes.
Pour into 10-inch greased tube pan.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake about 60 minutes more.
(Test for doneness after 45 minutes with knife inserted into cake.)
Let cake cool before removing from pan.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together.
Add the remaining ingredients and pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt oleo; add flour, mustard and salt. Stir in milk.
Cook until thickened slightly.
Remove from heat. Add 1 1/2 cups cheese, then add macaroni.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish; top with remaining cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crab souffle
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add crab.
Do not break up. Chop all vegetables.
Saute vegetables 5 minutes.
Stir in flour. Stir to mix.
Slowly add milk and cook until thick for 5 minutes. Stir in bread crumbs.
Combine peppers and stir into egg yolks. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Spoon mixture into baking dish.
Gently fold in crab.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake in preheated 375° oven until cheese is light golden brown and bubbly, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Wonderful casserole.

title: mints
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls and dip in granulated sugar.
Can be frozen.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Beat together eggs, pumpkin, sugar and oil until fluffy.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Spread batter into ungreased jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch).
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: paula's fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan. Add sugar and cocoa. Stir well and add eggs. Stir well, but do not beat. Add milk and vanilla; stir well again and pour in unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake for 10 minutes at 400°. Reduce to 350° and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cherry cheese spread
directions: Drain cherries saving the juice.
Quarter or half the cherries. With a fork, blend the softened cream cheese, cherries, enough juice to give it a medium pink color and nuts.
Serve on crackers.

title: bible cake
directions: This is an actual recipe that makes good, wholesome eating. You'll enjoy every bite, but you only find it in your bible.
Why not give it a try?
God bless.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 375° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesy pudding
directions: Trim crust off bread and cut in 4 pieces.
Butter each piece (40 pieces).
Grease souffle dish; alternate layers of bread and cheese beginning with cheese on bottom and bread on top.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard and pour over bread and cheese. Refrigerate overnight or at least 6 hours before baking.
Bring to room temperature and bake at 325 regress 40 minutes.
Mixture will rise to top of souffle dish but after taking it out of the oven it will fall.
Very delicious an easy to make.

title: easy mexican rice
directions: Saute onion and garlic in melted margarine in a skillet until onion is tender.
Pour hot water into a 2-quart casserole dish. Add garlic, rice, cooked onion and 3/4 cup of the chili seasoning mix package.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: truly tender ribs
directions: Wash ribs and cut according to your plan for use.
(Slab for grill.
Cut in smaller pieces for finger food.)
Put ribs in roasting pan and pour root beer over.
Add bay leaves and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Pour off root beer and remove bay leaves.
Add salt, pepper, basil, dill weed and garlic powder to taste. You can also add any of your favorite seasonings.
Add barbecue sauce.
Return to oven, uncovered, at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until crisp.
Mix remaining ingredients, except crackers and butter.
Mix well.
Add broccoli and spoon into greased baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Cover with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(This recipe doubled serves about 8.)

title: southwestern dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sour cream.
Stir in Cheddar and salsa.
Slice off top of bread.
Pick out inside of bread into bite size pieces.
Fill with cheese mixture.
Replace top.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with reserved bread, crackers or tortilla chips.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix margarine and graham cracker crumbs into a 9x13 inch pan. Chill thoroughly.
Mix margarine sugar and eggs.
Whip until light.
Pour over chilled crust and chill thoroughly.
After chilling place bananas on top.
Cover with pineapple.
Cover pineapple with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Add cherries.
Serves 15.

title: banana salad
directions: Slightly beat eggs; add sugar.
Mix and add vinegar and water. Cook over medium heat until bubbly.
Stir constantly to prevent sticking and lumps.
Cool.
Pour over peanuts and sliced bananas; mix lightly.

title: holiday ambrosia
directions: Cut oranges in small pieces and mix with all the ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Use the juice from the cherries. Refrigerate and serve.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Make well in dry ingredients and add 1 beaten egg and sour cream.
Mix well and place in greased large round cake pan or 2 small round pans.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, milk and butter and bring to boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cocoa, vanilla and oatmeal. Mix good and spoon on wax paper.

title: microwavable french chocolates
directions: Place chocolate chips in medium bowl; microwave on Medium-high (70%) until melted for 2 to 4 minutes, stirring twice.
Stir in walnuts, condensed milk, vanilla and salt.
Cool for 5 minutes. Shape into 3/4 to 1-inch balls.
Dip some in coconut, some in chopped nuts, the rest in powdered sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet and chill until set.
Makes 50 to 60 candies.

title: shrimp butter
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Stir well to blend.
Spoon into serving crock.
Cover; refrigerate for 24 hours.
Serve on thinly sliced white or rye bread.

title: cinnamon butter
directions: Mix well until fully blended.
Store in refrigerator.

title: zucchini bread with pineapple
directions: Beat eggs.
Add vanilla, oil and sugar; beat until foamy. Stir in zucchini and drained pineapple.
Sift together the flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg, then add nuts and raisins.
Add dry mixture to zucchini mixture; stir until blended. Do not overmix.
Divide batter evenly into 2 well-greased bread pans.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.

title: strawberry-rhubarb muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Combine egg, milk and oil in small bowl.
Stir into flour mixture with fork until just moistened.
Fold rhubarb and sliced strawberries into batter. Fill muffin tins or paper cups 2/3 full.
Press strawberry half into top of each muffin.
Sprinkle top generously with sugar. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine.
Shape into balls.
Cook at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package, using combined water, lemon juice and food coloring.
Add grated lemon peel.
Mix and then bake and cool as package directs.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Beat together lemonade and milk.
Fold together Cool Whip, lemonade and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix, chill and serve on your favorite crackers.

title: stuffed steak
directions: Flatten steak.
Lightly cook onion and celery.
Add bread cubes, seasonings, parsley and water.
Cut meat into 4 pieces. Spread with dressing mixture.
Roll up; fasten with toothpick. Roll in flour; brown in hot fat.
Dilute soup with 1 cup water and pour over meat.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Yield:

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place squash on baking sheet.
Add 1 tablespoon of each of remaining ingredients to squash, then place onions on butter and sugar.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes.

title: petite egg nog(approximately 950 calories)
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Cover and process until well blended.
Chill before serving.
Divide into 3 servings for full day's menu.

title: fried salt pork(poor man's chicken)
directions: Select pork with a streak of lean in it.
Use thick slices and cover with boiling water.
Let come to a boil again.
Remove from heat and pour off water. Fry until slices are brown and crisp. Drain on paper towel. Allow 3 or 4 slices per serving. Serve with green tomatoes or spoonbread or grits.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Place cheese, mayonnaise and onions in top of double boiler or microwave.
When melted, add crab.
This is best served with unsalted crackers.

title: baked ziti
directions: Prepare
pasta	as
directed
on
package;
cook only 7 minutes.
Drain.	Meanwhile,
brown
beef
and
drain.
Add seasonings, tomato sauce, tomato paste and water.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mix pasta, meat sauce,
cottage cheese, black olives and mushrooms in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese
over
Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: gayle's dog biscuits
directions: Note:
Will need one large microwave-safe mixing bowl.

title: sugar free orange applesauce muffins
directions: In a medium size mixing bowl, combine all dry ingredients and make a well in the center.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened (batter should be lumpy).
Spray 12 muffin cups with nonstick spray.
Fill cups about 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chuck wagon mac
directions: Prepare dinner as directed.
Brown ground beef.
Drain and add celery, pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in corn, tomato paste and water.
Mix with macaroni and cheese.
Serve hot. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients except pie filling.
Put 2/3 of dough into greased square pan (9 x 9-inch).
Spread pie filling over dough in pan.
Crumble remaining dough over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned.

title: layered club salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, layer lettuce, tomatoes, peas, chicken, bacon and green onions.
Spread mayonnaise on top.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Butter large roasting pan or use Pam spray.
Arrange cutlets over rice.
Pour soup and water over all.
Scatter onion soup on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 375°. Serves 4.

title: applesauce butter
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil on medium heat; cook for 1/2 hour, stirring often.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: easy gingerbread cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
By hand, mix dry cake mix, water, flour and butter.
Roll into balls and roll in sugar, then flatten slightly.
Or, roll out on floured surface and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake 6 to 9 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: gordon's eggnog
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks until pale.
Add sugar, one tablespoon at a time; beat after each addition.
Add bourbon and rum.
All this can be done a day ahead of time and refrigerated. Just before serving, whip cream and fold into egg mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold into mixture.
Serve in cups or goblets.
Top with sprinkle of nutmeg.

title: lo-cal breakfast bar
directions: Mix all ingredients, but peanut butter.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch sprayed dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Spread with peanut butter, if desired.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix coconut and Eagle Brand milk and spread on crust.
Bake about 15 minutes more.
Cool. Melt chips and 2 teaspoons of peanut butter and pour over coconut. Let set before cutting.

title: french toast
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well with a fork or an egg beater.
Cut the
bread in half and dip in the egg mixture for 1 to 3
minutes.
Remove
and
with the 1/2 cup of cooking oil in a frypan
medium
hot,
place
the
dipped bread in the frypan and brown until brown on both sides.
Serves 3.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Simmer chicken until tender.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Roll crackers into crumbs.
Add melted margarine and poppy seed.
Layer 1/2 crumbs on bottom of baking dish.
Add chicken to soup and sour cream.
Spread over crumbs.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May also be frozen.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt and set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in egg gradually; add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 30 cookies.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a salad bowl.
Chill until firm. Good as salad or dessert.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Pour boiling water until all ingredients are moistened.
Wet hands in cold water and pat out.
Drop into hot grease and fry until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice, onion and garlic in hot oil for 5 to 7 minutes over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Carefully add broth, water, tomato sauce and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Transfer the hot mixture to a 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven about 35 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed. If desired, fluff with a fork before serving.
Goes well with poultry or fish.

title: fudge
directions: In a saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with milk and salt. Remove from heat; stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into wax paper-lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill 2 hours.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: In a saucepan mix well gelatin, salt and sugar.
In a bowl, beat egg yolks with water and lemon juice.
Stir this mixture into gelatin mix.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture coats spoon and thickens.
Remove from heat.
In a large bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually sprinkle in 1/2 cup sugar. Beat until sugar is dissolved.
With spatula fold lemon mixture into egg whites just until blended.
Put into pie shell. Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with lemon rind.

title: rave review coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and walnuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pans 15 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.
Fill and top.
tags: Jell-O brand vanilla instant pudding mix

title: stir-fry beef
directions: Trim steak and cut into thin strips, 2-inches long.
Sear in oil in hot skillet or Wok.
Stir until lightly browned.
Separate onion slices into rings and add with celery and carrots.
Stir-fry until crisp-tender, or longer if you prefer.
Add green peppers and mushrooms.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together.
Make a well and pour in the oil, beaten eggs, vanilla, nuts and apples.
Stir together.
Do not use mixer.
Bake in a large pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: grandma fahrenkrog's vinegar vegetables
directions: Clean all the vegetables.
Leave the banana peppers whole. Cut the bell peppers into large chunks.
Cut the green tomatoes, onions and cauliflower into wedges.
Place mixture of all these raw vegetables into cleaned jars.
Place 2 to 3 hot peppers in each jar, if you like the heat.
They're what spice it up, so use as you desire.
Heat the vinegar, not to boiling, and pour over the vegetables in the jars.
Sprinkle a little salt in each jar. Place lids on and pressure can at 10 pounds of pressure for 5 minutes.
After opening jars, keep in refrigerator.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli in package until package feels warm, 4 to 5
1/2 minutes
on
Medium-low
Drain
broccoli well. Combine all
ingredients,
except half the onion rings, in a 3 quart casserole.
Microwave
at
High
for
6 minutes. Stir from outside
to
center of casserole to shorten cooking time and equalize heat.
Sprinkle with remaining onion rings. (Toppings are always
added at the end of cooking so they will not be
disturbed by stirring and will stay crisp.) Microwave at High (100%)
until center is hot, 2 to 4 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: red beet eggs
directions: Cover eggs with lukewarm water in
a saucepan.
Heat until water comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat and let stand for 20 minutes.
Run cold water over eggs to cool them quickly.
Peel eggs.

title: watermelon ice
directions: Blend at low speed 1 cup watermelon chunks with confectioners sugar, lemon juice and salt until mixture is smooth; add the remaining watermelon chunks and blend a few seconds longer, until smooth.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 9-inch baking pan; cover with foil and freeze until partially frozen (about 2 hours).

title: mexican pizza
directions: Prepare pizza crust according to package, browning crust 5 minutes.
Pan-fry ground beef, crumbling as it cooks.
Drain fat. Add taco seasoning mix and salsa; simmer 5 minutes.
Place meat mixture on top of crust.
Top with cheese.
Place in oven; bake until the cheese is melted.
Serve with toppings, such as lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream, etc.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup hot water.
Let cool.
Grind all fruit; add sugar.
Mix with jello.
Keep refrigerated.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix all together in large covered dish and let sit overnight.

title: beef 'n beer
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet and saute onions until tender. Coat beef cubes in flour and brown them in a separate skillet with oil and butter.
Add browned meat, salt, pepper and garlic to onions.
Add enough beer to cover.
Cover tightly and simmer until meat is tender.
Serves 6.

title: mulled cider
directions: Put in crock-pot.
Cover; heat on low for 2 to 5 hours or longer.

title: diabetic candy
directions: Beat peanut butter and milk together and add rest of ingredients.
Roll into balls and place on wax paper.
Mash with a fork and refrigerate.

title: microwave 10 minute peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and salt in 2-quart mixing bowl. Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave 2 to 5 minutes, stirring after 2nd and 4th minute until syrup and peanuts are lightly browned.
Stir in butter, vanilla and soda until light and foamy.
Spread to 1/4-inch thickness on large well buttered cookie sheet (work fast).
Break apart when cool.
For very thin peanut brittle, cool on cookie sheet 3 to 5 minutes. Lift from sheet and pull or stretch mixture to desired thinness.

title: mom's tomatoes
directions: Cook tomato juice, butter, sugar, salt and pepper.
Place crumbled bread slices in serving dish.
Pour whipping cream over bread, then hot tomatoes over both.

title: grilled p b & j
directions: Make peanut butter and jelly sandwich.
Butter each side of bread.
Place in skillet and brown it like a grilled cheese.

title: celebration punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine all ingredients.
Garnish with pineapple wedges and lime slices, if desired.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together oleo, crackers and poppy seed.
Place half mixture in 9 x 13-inch casserole and press down. Mix chicken, soup and sour cream in a bowl.
Pour on top of cracker mix.
Spoon remainder of cracker mix evenly on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: maryland lady crab cakes
directions: Remove all cartilage from crab meat.
In a bowl, mix crumbs, egg, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Add crab meat and mix gently but thoroughly.
If mixture is too dry, add a little more mayonnaise. Shape into 6 cakes.
Cook cakes in just enough fat to prevent sticking until browned, about 5 minutes on each side.

title: janet's seafood bisque
directions: Make into puree:
1/3 can salmon with small amount of milk in blender to make puree.
Use entire cans; make in thirds, as directed.
Saute scallops in butter and enough water to "pouch." Cut scallops in half before sauteing.
Pour hot milk (enough to cover crab meat) over crab.
Set aside.
Saute onion and celery in butter (chop both fine).

title: lasagna
directions: Mix together ground beef, onions, peppers, oregano, garlic salt and tomatoes.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
While sauce is simmering, add noodles to a separate large pot of water containing 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil.
Cook until tender and drain. Layer noodles, sauce, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese in three equal portions in large baking pan.
The finished product will have three layers.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.
Cool for 15 minutes before serving.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine the dry ingredients.
Combine the egg and oil with milk.
Add to the dry ingredients; mix well.
Insert wooden skewers into the wieners; cover the wieners with the corn meal mixture and fry in deep shortening until golden brown.

title: golden potato bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix cornflake crumbs and salt.
Brush potatoes with margarine; coat with crumbs.
Arrange in ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch square baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, until potatoes are tender, 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
