title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine and put into graham cracker crust.
Chill several hours.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and set aside.
In saucepan, cook celery in margarine until tender.
Mix soup and milk along with flour into celery until all is cooked and mixture is thick and bubbly.
Fold into drained tuna.
Add cooked noodles.
Stir carefully.
Put in casserole and bake uncovered at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, soda, salt and baking powder; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, coconut and Rice Krispies.
Drop onto cookie sheets.
Bake for about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: italian cookies
directions: Beat eggs and set aside.
Then beat the sugar and oil together; add the eggs and mix well.
Then add the remaining ingredients.
Bake on lightly greased pan at 325°.
Frost with vanilla frosting when cool.

title: glazed squash(for the barbecue)
directions: Cut squash lengthwise into strips about 1/2 inch thick.
Peel each strip.
Put the squash pieces on a large piece of doubled heavy aluminum foil.
Melt butter and stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over squash and wrap the foil loosely around the vegetable, making double folds to seal well.
Cook about 4 inches from hot coals for 45 minutes or until tender, turning the package halfway through cooking.
Note:
Bake in oven at 400° for about 1 hour, if desired.
Serves 2.

title: potato puffs
directions: Boil potatoes and mash with electric beater.
Add cream cheese and sour cream.
Beat at high speed.
Add salt and pepper. Spoon in a greased dish or pan. Dot with butter and dust with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fudge balls
directions: Melt over hot water the chips, milk and margarine; remove from heat and add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Simmer chicken until tender with celery, carrots, onion, salt and pepper in boiling water.
Simmer; do not boil.
Remove chicken from bone in large pieces; save broth.

title: gramma kopp's raisin filled cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with milk.
Mix well.
Cover and chill overnight.
Next day, roll out dough a portion at a time on floured board.
Cut with 3-inch round cookie cutter.
If you do not have a cutter, use the open end of a washed empty No. 2 size can to cut the cookies.
Put a spoonful of filling in the center of one circle of dough.
Top with another. Moisten edge with a little water and press with the tines of a fork.
Bake in oven at 375° for 17 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: new mexico peanut pie
directions: Combine
sugar, brown sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Add
milk
and
peanut
butter chips gradually. Cook and
stir on medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Reduce heat; cook
and
stir
2	minutes.
Beat	egg
yolks
lightly in	small bowl.
Stir
1 cup hot mixture into yolks gradually and
return egg
mixture
to saucepan.	Bring to gentle boil. Cook
and
stir on	low heat 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour mixture into baked pie shell and sprinkle with peanuts.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool to room temperature before serving.

title: peach punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water and add 2 cups ice water.
Add Hi-C and very soft ice milk.
Add chilled ginger ale right before serving.
Serves approximately 25 people.

title: mexacali spaghetti bake
directions: Cook spaghetti as package directs; drain.
Start heating oven to 325°.
Meanwhile, in oil in skillet, saute meat until mostly browned.
Add onion, pepper and garlic.
When meat is browned, add spaghetti, tomatoes, corn, salt, pepper, chili powder, olives and Worcestershire sauce; toss.
Put in a 3-quart casserole dish. Bake 1 hour, covered.

title: jenny's secret salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients well; form into patties.
Fry in hot olive oil until brown.
Drain excess oil from patties.
Serves 4 to 6.
Serve with buttered pasta.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Preparation: 30 minutes.
Cooking: 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: golden cream soup
directions: In large saucepan, add everything but cheese, milk and cornstarch.
Cover with cold water and lid.
Simmer until tender; let set 7 to 10 minutes.
Mix milk and cornstarch and add to vegetables.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Delicious and hearty!
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all of the above with hands.
Form small balls.
Place close together on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can be frozen and cooked as needed.
Cream cheese makes them easier to mix and gives a better flavor.

title: chicken stock
directions: In
a
5-quart stock pot or Dutch oven, combine chicken pieces,
celery,
carrots,	salt and pepper;
add water.
Stud each
onion
third	with a whole clove.
Add to pot.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce
heat, cover and simmer about 1 hour or until chicken
is
tender.
Lift	out
chicken pieces with a slotted spoon.
Strain
stock through a sieve lined with 1 or 2 layers of cheesecloth; discard vegetables.
Skim off fat with a metal spoon, or
chill stock and lift off the solidified fat.
When chicken is	cool
enough to handle, remove chicken from bones and
save meat
for
another	use,
if desired.
Makes 5 cups stock.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and add onions.
Drain well.
Add taco and Ranch mixes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix in large pot. Makes a lot.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Serve with corn bread or tortilla chips.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Wash and clean mushrooms.
Add all ingredients to pot and simmer 25 minutes on low heat.
Keep covered so liquids remain. Serve at room temperature or chilled.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Fill 3-quart crock-pot with peeled, quartered apples (any kind). Add ingredients. Cover crock-pot and cook all night on low. Continue all next day. Use blender or mixer to remove lumps. With lid removed, cook another 1 1/2 to 2 hours on high heat to boil down. You can double recipe. Yields 7 pints.

title: chocolate kahlua cookies
directions: In a large bowl, place the Kahlua, oil, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and flour.
Mix well, then add the almonds and chocolate chips.
Blend well.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Leave as is or frost with your favorite icing (canned or homemade).
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: dumplings for fruit
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter until resembles corn meal.
With fork, stir in milk.
Form mixture into ball.
Roll onto floured board, 1/4-inch thick.
Cover fruit, cut edges and cut vent in center.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
(3 cups sweet fruit)

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss all lightly together, then chill for several hours.
Just before serving, add 4 tablespoons of mayonnaise and salt to taste.
After mixing, if salad needs a little more zip, add a little lemon juice and sugar.
Serves 10.

title: daisy's yum yum salad
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water for 10 minutes. Heat pineapple. Add sugar and lemon juice. Add soaked gelatin to hot mixture. When cool and beginning to set, add cheese, whipped cream, olives and nuts. Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and place in refrigerator to finish congealing. Serves 15.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar together and pour over broccoli and cooked crisp bacon, onions, sunflower seeds and raisins.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Spray nonstick skillet with Pam.
Combine all ingredients listed in the skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over linguini, angel hair pasta or any cooked pasta.

title: party sandwiches(ham filling)
directions: Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: perfect peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter, peanut butter, sugar and 1/4 cup brown sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla until thoroughly blended.

title: brownies
directions: Beat all ingredients together at medium speed on mixer for 1 minute.
Spread in greased 15 x 10-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cornmeal bread
directions: Mix liquids and stir into mixed dry ingredients.
Place in flat pan, about 8 x 11-inch and bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Crumb the bread in blender.
Put 1/2 can of tomato sauce, onion, egg, salt and pepper in blender and chop.
Add to ground beef and bread crumbs.
Mix well and form into loaf.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt peanut butter and margarine in bowl in microwave oven.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread in pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: peanut butter creams
directions: Beat egg.
Beat in 1 cup sugar, salt, vanilla, peanut butter and butter.
Add other 1 cup of remaining sugar.
Add more sugar if not firm enough.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in chopped peanuts.
Yields 3 dozen candies.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and baking powder. Add pumpkin, oil, eggs, nuts and raisins.
Pour into pan.
Bake 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: spinach pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake until knife comes out clean.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Grind cookies in a food processor or blender; mix with melted oleo.
Set aside 1/2 cup crumbs.
Press the rest of the crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator to set.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all.
Best to refrigerate overnight.
Chopped veggies all as small as possible makes it better.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix together hominy, soup, chilies, pimento, salt and pepper. Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: peanut butter granola
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Stir together oats, wheat germ and sunflower seeds in a large mixing bowl.
In a saucepan, heat oil and honey, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well. Spread over a cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes so that the granola browns evenly.
Remove from oven and cool thoroughly.
Mix raisins and nuts in.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 5 cups.

title: mounds
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and wax in top of a double boiler.
Dip balls into mixture, covering completely.
Place on waxed paper to dry.

title: quick and easy refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix together cucumbers, onions and green pepper.
Mix together all other ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
It looks like it doesn't have enough liquid, but it settles down.
Store in refrigerator.
Will keep up to 1 year in refrigerator.
Tastes like bread and butter pickles, and you can eat them right away. These do not get cooked at any time.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm.
Roll into balls.
Place 3 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Mash with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add butter.
Mix in with hands.
Add raisins and beat egg and milk together.
Add to the ingredients with fork; mix until moistened.
Pour into prepared pan and slice the top of batter with knife.
Bake at 350° in large greased loaf pan for about 1 hour.

title: hotsy totsy shrimp
directions: Put oil in pan and sprinkle about 1 tablespoon crushed red hot pepper.
Saute about 1 minute or until light brown.
In pot, put tomatoes and seasoning, then pour in oil and pepper.
Simmer about 45 minutes.
Add shrimp and heat about 15 minutes.

title: broccoli muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, oats, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a small bowl, mix milk, oil and egg; stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fold in broccoli and cheese. Spoon into greased or paper-lined muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched. Yield:
1 dozen.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Heat vinegar, oil and sugar.
Pour over cooked, drained spaghetti.
Stir in pimentos, green pepper and salad spice. Refrigerate overnight.

title: devilish eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Carefully remove yolks and mash with mayo, sour cream, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Mound mixture into egg whites (use a pastry bag for decorative effect).
Sprinkle eggs with paprika.
Refrigerate until served.

title: 2 x 4 soup
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat thoroughly until cheese is melted.

title: sweet and zesty barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Brush on your favorite dish.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Into a large pizza pan, press crescent rolls.
Bake at 400° until browned.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and salad dressing well. Then smooth mixture over cooled pizza crust.
Sprinkle garlic salt over top of this.
Add vegetables of your choice and generously sprinkle Mozzarella cheese or any shredded cheese that you choose on top.

title: broccoli with curry sauce
directions: Steam broccoli until tender.
In a small bowl add mayonnaise, butter, lemon juice and curry.
Add in 5 shakes of garlic salt. Serve over cooked broccoli.

title: cream sauce
directions: Beat eggs and flour together until smooth.
Add sugar, vanilla and 1 cup of milk.
Mix well.
Pour into saucepan and add rest of milk.
Stir constantly until thick on low heat.
Serve warm or cold over cake.

title: oven chow mein
directions: Combine meats and brown lightly in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Stir occasionally.
Add water, if needed.

title: teen c~b~s soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in Dutch oven and heat on low for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: romanian doughnuts(gogosi)
directions: Sprinkle flower on a clean work surface and roll out one thick sheet of sweet bread dough.
Cut rounds of dough with a doughnut cutter or the bottom of a glass and place them on a cloth (Romanian doughnuts have no hole).
Cover and let them rise until double in size.
Heat oil in a pot and fry the doughnuts, turn on both sides.
Keep heat low.
When they are ready, remove with a slotted spoon and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve hot or cold.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop the popcorn and lay out onto a baking sheet.
Pour caramels over it and bake on 325° until melted.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Scrape icing off cookies, then crush all cookies real fine. Put in bowl and mix butter with crushed cookies.
Spread on bottom of 9 1/2 x 11-inch cake pan, then stick in freezer.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken in crock-pot until done. Debone. In one bowl, mix flour, garlic and milk. In another, mix soup and broth. Melt butter in 9 x 13 baking dish. Pull apart chicken; put into pan. Pour flour mixture over chicken; pour soup mixture over that. Bake at 425° for about 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Serve with vegetables.

title: hungi-gungi
directions: Panbroil meat, onion, and green pepper.
Cook macaroni per pkg. instructions. Combine meat, macaroni, tomatoes and sauce. Heat together. Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese if you like.

title: sweeter than mommy's kiss chocolate cake
directions: Prepare devil's food cake mix according to package directions. When baked, punch holes in the cake with the end of a wooden spoon.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken until done; bone and coarsely chop chicken.
(We usually use whole bird or if you prefer, chicken breasts.)
Retain 2 cups broth.
Spread chicken in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Add the slightly crushed egg noodles on top of chicken.
Saute onion and celery in small amount of butter.
Mix the cream of chicken soup, peas, mushroom soup, sauteed onion and celery and 2 cups broth; pour over chicken and noodles.
If you use the almonds, add to this mixture also.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly and the cheese melts.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Then layer peas, peppers, onion and cheese in order.
Mix mayo and sugar together and spread over top.
Sprinkle with bacon bits, if desired.

title: creamy cheesy potatoes(tastes great with ham)
directions: In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, spread hash browns; add half of the melted butter over the potatoes.
Sprinkle with chopped onion. Spread cream of chicken soup over potatoes, then sprinkle cheese over this and then spread sour cream over all.
Sprinkle Special K on top, then drizzle remaining butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco, and butter.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs one at a time and continue mixing.
Add 1/2 of flour mixture with 1/2 cup of the milk and mix.
Add remaining flour mixture and milk; mix until well blended.
Bake one hour and 15 minutes at 325° in well greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Put enchilada sauce on bottom of 8 1/2 x 12-inch pan.
Coat tortilla with sauce, then layer everything in order on tortilla and roll up.
Lay in pan, side by side.
Put remaining sauce on top and remaining cheeses.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted.
These freeze well, too.

title: ho-bo bread
directions: Soak raisins in water and soda overnight.
Then add flour 1 cup at a time, stirring well after each addition.
Bake in coffee cans (three 1 pound cans) or 15 ounce vegetable cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes, then turn out on board.
Delicious while warm.
May add maraschino cherries if desired.

title: grilled burgers
directions: Place burgers on grill.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
I like extra garlic salt.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Put a layer of graham crackers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish. Mix pudding mix with milk; beat with mixer on low speed until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put layer of pudding on top of crackers, then another layer of crackers, followed by more pudding.
Continue to layer crackers and pudding, ending with layer of crackers until pudding is used up.
Spread chocolate frosting on top.
Refrigerate.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Blend ingredients in a large bowl. Beat 2 minutes on medium speed. Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan (15 minutes). Split into 3 layers.
Spread 1 cup frosting between each layer. Spoon the rest into center.
Garnish with crushed nuts.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix sugar with cornstarch in a pan.
Add water.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Add gelatin to mixture and stir until dissolved.
Chill until partially thickened.
Place peaches in pie shell and cover with gelatin mixture.
Chill until firm. Garnish with whipped cream.
Delicious!

title: lone star pecan pie
directions: Blend all ingredients and bake until a silver knife inserted comes out clean, about 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and milk.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Fold in berries.

title: mushroom quiche
directions: Brush inside of pie shell with small amount of beaten eggs. Prick bottom
and sides with fork. Saute mushrooms and onions in butter until mushrooms are lightly browned and onions tender (6 to 8 minutes). Stir together mushrooms, onions and Swiss cheese.
Put into pie shell. To the beaten eggs, add all remaining ingredients. Beat well and pour over mushroom mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: peas and onions supreme
directions: Drain onions; reserve liquid.
Put onions and peas in a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Melt butter. Add flour and blend.
Add water or milk to liquid from onions to make 1 cup.
Cream and cook until thick.
Add wine.
Stir and pour over onions and peas.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mayhaw-pecan tarts or pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and margarine; stir in flour and mix until smooth.
Form into ball.
Use fingers to press 3/4-inch marble-sized portions into small muffin tins.
Fill with mayhaw-pecan pie filling and bake.
Makes enough for 48 thin pastry shells.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses(cookies)
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with back of floured fork to make crisscrosses.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° about 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together, then mix in cold water. Beat in egg yolks.
Add vanilla and melted butter and milk.
Cook at 350° in unbaked pie shell.
Use 1/3 cup sugar to make meringue.

title: corn and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli 15 to 20 minutes.
Open kettle and salt lightly. Cut broccoli into 1-inch pieces.
Sprinkle top with 6 crushed crackers and 1 tablespoon melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: coconut or lemon pound cake
directions: Bake 9 inch cake layer, using recipe of your choice.
Cut layer in half.
Ice pieces together leaving rounded edge to top. Decorate with pink jelly beans for eyes and ears.
(Add stiff paper cut outs for actual ears.
Jelly beans at the base will make them look more like ears.)
Use black jellybean for nose and toothpicks as whiskers.
Red for mouth, white for tail, green coconut for grass under rabbit.

title: apricot salad
directions: Refrigerate evaporated skim milk overnight.
Stir apricot gelatin in water and boil.
Let cool.
Whip the cold evaporated skim milk.
Cream sugar, Neufchatel cheese, apricot baby food, crushed pineapple and cooked gelatin.
Fold in whipped milk. Chill and serve.
Serves 28 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together the next 3 ingredients.
Add to other mixture.
Add last 2 ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy chicken salad
directions: Combine and toss lightly all ingredients with potato chips on top.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until tender.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion and saute.
Add green pepper and soup, mixing well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish. Place half the noodles in bottom of dish, then cover with half of chicken.
Season with salt and pepper, then add half of mushroom soup mixture and half the grated cheese.
Repeat layers, using remaining ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and serve.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Blend in well-beaten eggs. Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to mixture, blend in vanilla, oatmeal, bran flakes and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Put chicken in 8-quart pot.
Cover with water.
Add onion and celery and cook until meat is well done and can be removed from bone.
Remove chicken.
Cool and bone.
Cut chicken into pieces and return to pot.
If needed, add 13 ounce can of chicken broth.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in 2 round cake pans.
Let cool, then break into bite size pieces and set aside.
Prepare gelatin as directed on box.
Prepare pudding as directed on box.
Layer in punch bowl 1/2 cake, 1/2 pudding, 1/2 fruit and 1/2 gelatin.
Add second layer cake, pudding, fruit and gelatin.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with some fruit, if desired.

title: lemon snack crackers
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Add crackers, coating thoroughly.
Bake 10 minutes in a shallow baking pan at 300°.
Stir once during baking.
Cool and store in an airtight container.

title: cedric adams hot dish
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter.
Add ground chuck.
Do not brown.
Just heat.
Spread 3 cups cabbage in bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with meat mixture.
Add rest of cabbage; pour over tomato soup.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Stir after 1/2 hour.

title: no peek stew
directions: Cut meat and vegetables into medium chunks.
Put all ingredients in covered roasting pan.
Cover and bake at 250° for 4 1/2 hours.
You may stir stew during the last hour to check on it. Also, add water, if needed, and adjust seasonings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put in a crock-pot on low. Cook for 4 to 6 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: breakfast hoagie
directions: Fry crumbled sausage; drain well.
Mix eggs and milk; scramble.
Split hoagie lengthwise; place crumbled sausage and eggs on bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cut in 4 parts.
Great for breakfast on the run.

title: lollipop cookies
directions: You will need 30 lollipop sticks 4 1/2 inches long.

title: french toast
directions: With a fork, lightly beat the eggs, salt, nutmeg, sugar and milk until well mixed.
Melt butter in frying pan and heat until butter begins to brown.
Dip each slice of bread in the egg mixture until well soaked and place in the frying pan to cook. Cook one side until lightly browned and flip over to brown the other side.
You can keep the cooked French toast hot in a warm oven until you've cooked all your bread.
Serve hot with butter and syrup.
Yield: 2 to 3 servings.

title: rum cup
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Cook 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add rum. Combine fruits in bowl.
Pour syrup over and marinate in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours.

title: mom's sweet potatoes
directions: Heat canned sweet potatoes or peel and cut fresh sweet potatoes and boil them 30 minutes in water enough to cover them.
When done, drain them and mash them up.
Add butter, sugar and vanilla.
Mash it up and add raisins and nuts.
Butter your casserole and pour it in.
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes.

title: tarter sauce
directions: Drain all of the chopped ingredients.
Fold in mayonnaise. Mix well and chill.
Serve with fish.

title: greek corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Use a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: crab casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add salt, pepper and Accent.
Smooth in flour and cream, stirring constantly until thick and smooth.
Drain crab and add to sauce.
Add mushrooms.
Butter sides and bottom of a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with some cheese.
Add crab mixture. Top with crumbs, cheese and paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°. This may be prepared ahead of time and cooked at the last minute.

title: strawberry pie glaze
directions: Mix and cook to desired thickness; add red food coloring.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add sugar and cream; bring to a boil and cook for 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Mix together the cornstarch, flour and salt.
Stir in gradually 1 cup of cold milk. Stir until smooth.
Scald 1 cup milk and add to brown sugar mixture.
Then add cornstarch and milk mixture.
Cook until it thickens, stirring constantly.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add a little of the pudding mixture to this and mix well.
Put rest of pudding mix in top of double boiler and then add egg mixture. Cook until thickened.
Add vanilla.
Cool.
Pour into pie shell and top with meringue.

title: marinara sauce
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, in a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat in hot oil, cook onion and garlic until tender, stirring occasionally.

title: cincinnati dream bars
directions: To make crust, cut 1 stick of margarine into flour (texture will be crumbly) and spread into bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: thai chicken sate
directions: You will also need 12 (12-inch) bamboo skewers.

title: tortilla soup
directions: In Dutch oven, brown chicken and bacon about 5 minutes or until fully cooked. Add broth and seasonings; bring to boil. Add vegetables and picante sauce; simmer 5 minutes, covered, or until vegetables are tender-crisp. Ladle into bowls and sprinkle with cheese and tortilla chips. Makes 6 servings.

title: spicy hot crock-pot gumbo
directions: Put all but shrimp in crock-pot and stir well. Cover and cook on high 2 to 3 hours or until rice is tender. Add shrimp and cook on high 15 to 25 minutes until shrimp are cooked through. Add file to pot or sprinkle in gumbo bowls or cups. Serve immediately with oyster crackers.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles, then drain. Chop other ingredients and mix well. Pour Italian dressing over this and chill.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan while preheating oven to 350°.
Coat
pan with butter and pour out excess (reserve). Pour can
of
cherries
in
baking pan.	Sprinkle dry cake mix with nuts over cherries.
Pour reserved melted butter over dry cake mix.
Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool completely at room temperature.
Serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add cream cheese and stir until mixed. Let cool. Add pineapple, sugar, vanilla and pecans; stir well. Add Sprite; stir well. Chill until set.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Place oil in skillet over high heat.
Add garlic and stir-fry 30 minutes.
Add vegetables to time it takes to cool.
Mix cornstarch and soy sauce, add to vegetables.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender but crisp, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: spinach-orange toss
directions: Place torn spinach in a large salad bowl. Add Mandarin orange sections and sliced mushrooms. Toss lightly. Cover and chill.

title: mexican sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage in a skillet and drain well.
Cut cheese into small cubes.
In a crock-pot, add all ingredients and simmer on low heat for 15 minutes.
Stir well and continue to simmer until it reaches a thick consistency and all cheese is melted.
Serve hot with tortilla chips for dipping.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine and cook 45 minutes at 350°, covered.
Stir often.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Blend well.
Serve with fresh apple wedges.
Sprinkle apples with Fruit Fresh or store in salted water until ready to serve.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put sugar and cocoa in mixing bowl.
Make a well in the center and pour Carnation milk in well.
Top with stick of butter.
Cook on High 2 minutes, uncovered.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Prepare and bake pie shell.
Cool.
Wash and hull strawberries.
Reserve half.
Mash the rest in a saucepan.
Mix sugar and cornstarch and add to mashed berries.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Stir in lemon juice. Cool completely.
Add remaining berries.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Chill to settle.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: creme brulee
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Spray 8 (4 ounce) ramekins with nonstick spray. Have two
9-inch baking dishes ready.

title: homemade chili soup
directions: Boil meat, onions and 2 quarts of water for 30 minutes, then add other ingredients.

title: max's homemade cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix together warm water, yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Let stand.
Stir remaining ingredients together and add flour until stiff enough to turn on floured board.
Knead enough to not be sticky.
Place in greased bowl and let double in size.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage into a large skillet or saucepan; cook over medium heat until brown and well done.
Stir in flour; cook over medium-low heat about 6 minutes or until mixture bubbles and turns golden.
Stir in milk.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
To serve, slice biscuits or crumble biscuits and spoon gravy over biscuits.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: catfish
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix with rest of ingredients and put on top of fish.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fluffy coconut frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in sugar, milk and almond extract.
Fold in whipped topping and coconut.

title: hot chicken wings
directions: Broil wings or drumettes until cooked through.
While wings are broiling mix remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer sauce. Place wings in baking dish and pour sauce over contents.
Cover dish with foil and bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: spring pea salad
directions: Rinse peas in hot water; drain.
Combine vegetables, nuts and bacon with sour cream.
Mix mustard and dressing together and pour over salad mixture.
Toss gently and chill.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Slice cucumbers very thin.
Mix dressing with softened cream cheese.
Spread liberally over cocktail rye.
Place cucumber on top and sprinkle with dill weed. Serve.

title: easy man lasagna
directions: Make your own sauce with or without meat.
In a large bowl put Ricotta, eggs, cheese, parsley, garlic powder, oregano and pepper. Mix all together.
If your sauce has meatballs, remove about 4 from sauce.
Mash them and mix to Ricotta mixture.
Add a 1/2 cup of sauce and mix all together.
Cook noodles for 4 minutes.
Drain. Put back in pan with margarine so that noodles won't stick.
Mix. Add 1 cup sauce.
In large pan pour 1 cup sauce.
Add Ricotta mixture to noodles in pan.
Mix well.
Return to lasagna pan.
Put some sauce on bottom.
Spread evenly.
Add a little sauce on top. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain, Mix all ingredients together in crock pot and melt on high.

title: breakfast buns
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together the flour, 1/2 cup of sugar and baking powder.
Cut in butter.
Combine eggs, vanilla and milk.
Add to dry ingredients and stir just until moistened.
Add raisins.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.

title: cherry or strawberry delight
directions: Mix and set in refrigerator for a while.
Whip 1 package Dream Whip.
Add to other ingredients and spread over crust.

title: chili hash
directions: Cook onion in butter until soft.
Add chili and potatoes. Cook and stir until hot and until flavors blend.
Serve with mustard if desired.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: banana supreme pudding
directions: Slice off the peel and white membrane from oranges with a sharp knife; cut crosswise into thin slices, about 1/4-inch thick. Place in a large serving dish, spreading out as much as possible. Sprinkle the lemon rind and lemon juice over oranges.
Combine the sugar and ground ginger or candied ginger.
Sprinkle over oranges.
Let stand in refrigerator for several hours, basting with juice.
Can be covered and refrigerated overnight.

title: clam-ham dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with potato chips or crackers.
One cup of chopped shrimp may be substituted.

title: shrimp saute with orzo
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add orzo; cook until al dente.
Drain; toss with 1 teaspoon oil and add salt and pepper to taste.
Heat remaining oil in a large skillet.
Add garlic; cook over low heat for 1 minute.
Add shrimp, salt and pepper to taste and 2 tablespoons parsley.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Turn and cook for 3 minutes or until opaque.
Remove from pan and keep warm.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Work until texture is of pie dough.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Divide and press into tins.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip pound cakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease four 3 1/2-cup mini loaf pans.

title: make-ahead eggs benedict
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish arrange muffins, cut side up. Place 2 slices bacon on each muffin half.

title: sticky buns
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease Bundt pan.
Spread pecans on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Spread 1/2 cup brown sugar, butter (cut up) and butterscotch pudding on the bottom of pan.
Place slightly thawed frozen bread dough (cut up) around pan.
Cover with paper towel.
Let sit for 5 hours.
Bake for 30 minutes and turn upside down on plate immediately.

title: baked butter beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Save grease and saute celery, onion and bell pepper.
Add flour, tomato sauce, sugar, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add butter beans.
Cook in casserole with bacon strips across the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.
Serves 10.

title: crunchy ice cream pie
directions: Beat sugar and margarine well.
Add other ingredients.
Press firmly around pie plate.
Take out 1/4 cup of mixture for topping. Chill.
Add the ice cream and freeze.

title: brown sugar fudge
directions: Boil sugar and cream until soft ball stage.
Add butter, nuts and vanilla.
Cool and beat.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and add boiling water to make a thick paste.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot oil (375°).

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash, cube and cook squash until tender; drain well.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix as any cookies and bake on a cookie sheet in a 350° oven for about 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: hot appetizer pie
directions: Mix cream cheese with milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in 8-inch Pyrex pie pan.
For topping, brown 1/4 cup chopped pecans in 2 tablespoons butter.
Pour on top of mixture. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: praline pumpkin pie
directions: First prepare pastry shell.
Cream margarine with brown sugar. Add pecans.
Press over pastry shell in even layer.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Cool.
Next, mix rest of ingredients and pour into cooled pastry.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Cool and serve.
Top with whipped cream.

title: janet's mexicorn
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all the ingredients.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter; stir in powdered sugar.
Spread in a cookie sheet and cover with chocolate chips.
Put in oven to soften, then spread chocolate over the bars.

title: killed cabbage
directions: Saute small bacon pieces until limp, but not brown.
Add cabbage (chopped fine) and onions (chopped).
Add pepper and water.
Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes until cabbage is soft.
I serve over fried potatoes.
Serves 4 generously.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mash garlic.
Slice zucchini thinly.
Chop onion.
Beat eggs. Chop parsley.
Mix all ingredients and spread in 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with paprika on top.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine and dot with butter.
Place cut-up fryer on top and bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix applesauce and cinnamon to form a stiff dough.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Make hole with a straw for ribbon.
Carefully put on rack to dry.
Let air dry several days, turning occasionally.
Makes 12 sweet smelling ornaments.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine and 2 cups peanut butter over low heat and pour over ingredients.
Stir with spoon until powdered sugar is mixed in good.
Make into balls.
Make paraffin and chocolate chips melt in a double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate; put on wax paper. Makes 5 dozen balls.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil fryer (optional:
pull meat off bones).
Add to boiled water the soup and pepper to taste.
Slice flour tortillas into thin strips and add to mixture.
Never tasted dumplings soooo good and tender!!!

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Fry chicken breast in cooking oil with green onions.
When done, put chicken breast and green onions into a casserole dish. Mix broccoli and cream of mushroom soup together.
Then pour over chicken and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
This is also good served over rice.

title: hamburger sour cream casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Mix the next 5 ingredients. Cook noodles and layer over meat.
Pour tomato juice mixture over meat and noodles.
Add green pepper on top and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add sour cream and mushrooms.
Simmer another 10 minutes.
Pour in 2 large or 3 small casserole dishes.
You can freeze at this point or add cheese of your choice and bake in moderate oven until golden.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash in a little boiling water until tender; drain. Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups stuffing cubes, soup, sour cream and 1/2 of butter.
Gently stir in carrots and onion.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Melt remaining butter; add rest of the stuffing and gently toss and top casserole.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oven-baked parmesan potatoes
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine Parmesan cheese, flour, salt, pepper and parsley.
Dredge cut potatoes in melted butter, then dip into the flour-cheese and seasoning mix.
Return to pan in single layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn over. Bake another 30 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.

title: beef jerky
directions: Mix ingredients by hand until well mixed.
Roll into 3 rolls. Wrap in Saran Wrap for microwave or foil for oven.
Refrigerate overnight.
Punch holes in wrap.
Bake in microwave or oven in broiler type pan so juice can run out until done.
Cool, slice and serve on crackers or snacks.
Can be frozen.
Do not overbake in microwave.
Just until meat is done.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in lightly greased baking dish; top with cheese. Combine soup and water; mix well and spoon evenly over chicken. Top with stuffing and sprinkle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Season with garlic salt and black pepper.
Put flour, garlic salt and pepper in brown bag.
Put chicken in brown bag and shake until well coated.
Heat cooking oil until hot, usually 350°.
Fry in deep fryer or cooker until golden brown; turn only once.
Cook approximately 20 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: philippino style chicken adoba
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces, leaving bone in.
Cube pork into bite size pieces.
Saute chicken and pork until brown.
Layer chicken, pork and onion in large pot.
Mix vinegar and soy sauce and pour over chicken-pork mixture.
Simmer until done.
Serve over boiled rice.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets in boiling water.
Peel and dice or slice thinly.
Add vinegar and seasonings.
Fry bacon until crisp. Combine potatoes, bacon, 2 tablespoons bacon fat and onion; mix well.
Serve on lettuce with big frankfurters or German sausage. Serves 8.

title: dump cake
directions: In a pan that has been sprayed with a nonstick coating, dump the first 2 items into the pan.
Dump cake mix and spread evenly with a fork.
Dump the pecans on top.
Lay butter pats over top. Cover pan loosely with foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
The last 15 minutes of baking, remove foil so cake can brown.

title: butterscotch bubble loaf(coffee cake)
directions: Generously butter a 12-cup Bundt pan or 9 x 9-inch pan. Arrange cherries if used, on bottom.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Cut loaf of bread into 24 pieces.
Place pieces in pan. Sprinkle with pudding mix, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Drizzle with remaining butter.
Let rise in a warm place until about double in size (about 3 to 4 hours).
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand about a minute.
Turn onto plate or wire rack which has been lined with waxed paper.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mixture will be thick.
With hands, roll into small balls.
Press slightly with thumb.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 250° to 300° oven until lightly brown.

title: scalloped tuna and potato casserole
directions: Cook sliced potatoes in water for 10 minutes; drain (set aside).
Add milk, salt, pepper and butter in saucepan.
Add flour.
Mix until smooth and mixture thickens.
Take off stove. Arrange potatoes, tuna and onions in alternate layers in greased 2 quart casserole.
Pour sauce overall.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until onions are soft.
Cover with lid.

title: grapefruit, shrimp and avocado salad
directions: Drain grapefruit sections.
Add enough fresh grapefruit juice to the drained grapefruit juice to make 3 cups of liquid.
Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup of juice over low heat until completely dissolved. Add remaining 2 cups of juice, sugar and salt.
Put in refrigerator until it starts to set.
Add the grapefruit sections, shrimp, avocado and onion tops.
Put into a 6-cup mold and refrigerate. Unmold and decorate with parsley and pimento.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass baking pan.
Spread pineapple rings over the bottom of baking pan.
Pour pie filling over pineapple and spread evenly.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over filling.
Pour melted oleo over cake mix.
Top with chopped nuts (if desired). Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until evenly browned.
Serve as is, or with whipped cream, Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: tortilla appetizers
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and spread thin on tortillas and roll.
Refrigerate between layers of damp paper towels.
Slice each roll in 1/2-inch slices when ready to serve.
Place slices on serving tray
and dip in bowl of picante sauce.
Makes a lot.

title: 6 minute hot rolls
directions: Mix water,
yeast
and sugar into mixer bowl.
Add half of the flour;
beat well.
Add egg, salt and shortening.	Add rest of flour.
Mix
well.	Let rise 30 minutes.
Punch down. Spoon into muffin pans.
Makes 12 muffins.
Bake until brown.

title: hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients in a big bowl.
Bake at 350° for an hour or until cooked.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Add water, a small amount at a time.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Knead dough into ball the size of an egg.
Roll on lightly floured surface to 6-inch circle.
Cook on a griddle, turning once until it has light brown flecks on each side.
This is Miguel's favorite.
It came from Honduras like he did!

title: ambrosia
directions: Stir together and refrigerate.

title: fudge pudding cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and cocoa 3 times.
Combine milk, vanilla and margarine.
Add to dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Stir in chopped walnuts. Spread in a buttered 6-cup casserole.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Put the can of crushed pineapple in the bottom of a 13 x 9 1/2-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Put the can of blueberry pie filling on top of the pineapple. Sprinkle the entire box of cake mix over the top of the blueberry pie filling. Cut
up 2 sticks of margarine over the top of the cake mix.
Place in a 350° oven and bake 1 hour.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Add onion and saute until clear. Add almonds, celery and rice; cook for 2 minutes. Pour consomme or bouillon and undrained mushrooms into skillet. Transfer to covered casserole and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir together sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Add to melted margarine.
Next add peaches and stir very slightly.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Serve with ice cream.

title: bean dip
directions: Heat together soup, tomato sauce, cheese and chili powder. Keep warm.
Serve with corn chips.
Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: coconut snowball cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions.
Mix sour cream, sugar and coconut and spread
this between layers, saving one third of mixture, and mix Cool Whip with this for icing.
Decorate with candied cherries, if desired.

title: wheat yogurt muffins(lo-cal)
directions: Combine flour, wheat germ, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt in large bowl.
Add yogurt, butter, egg and raisins.
Stir just to moisten.
Fill paper lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.
Calories 125 each.

title: super hot slaw
directions: Place all ingredients in electric blender until smooth. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: chicken mexicali
directions: Cook chicken; remove skin and bone.
Preheat oven to 350°. Arrange tortilla chips on bottom and sides of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong baking dish.
Cover tortilla chips with broken pieces of chicken.
Combine liquid ingredients.
Add onion and bell pepper. Pour over chicken.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl, add pudding mix, beat with wire whisk until well blended, approximately 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin and spices with wire whisk.
Mix well, spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: cheese strips
directions: Fry and crumble bacon.
Grate cheese into a bowl.
Add bacon, onion, almonds, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Trim bread crust.
Spread mixture on bread.
Cut into 4 strips.
Place strips on cookie sheet.
Freeze for 1 hour. Store in plastic bags.
When ready to serve, place frozen strips on a cookie sheet and bake 400°
for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: italian garden salad
directions: Chop tomatoes, green peppers, red onion and cucumbers coarsely.
Pour in Italian dressing and sugar.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Grind the rhubarb in a food processor or grinder.
Strain through a jelly bag, reserving 3 1/2 cups of juice.
Pour juice into a large kettle; add sugar and food coloring, if desired. Bring to a boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Add pectin; bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from the heat; let stand a few minutes.
Skim off foam.
Pour hot into jot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Adjust caps.
Process for 10 minutes in a boiling water bath. Yield:
8 half-pints.

title: crayzee cherry pie
directions: Place pie filling in pie crust.
Mix Dream Whip, sugar and cream cheese together.
Top pie filling with cream cheese mixture. Chill.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and cut in Crisco until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in sour cream with fork.
Add buttermilk gradually until mixture is slightly wet.
Turn out on floured board and knead a little.
Pat out on board and cut with small glass or biscuit cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 450° for 10 minutes.
Yields 12 or 13.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, press out rolls to make bottom crust. Press all rolls together.
Spread meat evenly on crust.
Cover with cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour carefully over crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until eggs are set and crust is golden.

title: grandma tritts' corn relish
directions: Steam corn for 15 minutes.
Cut off cob, add rest of recipe. Boil 20 minutes.
Yields 5 quarts.

title: applesauce bars
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend.
Mix together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add applesauce, raisins
and peanut granules.

title: marinated italian chicken
directions: Pour dressing over chicken breasts.
Let marinate for 15 minutes.
Place on rack in broiler pan.
Broil 5 to 7 minutes on each side until juices are clear.

title: mackerel-noodle bake
directions: Cook celery and onion in 2 tablespoons water, covered, until tender, 5 to 7 minutes.
Combine with next 4 ingredients, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt oleo. Saute onion and garlic. Add flour and set aside. Cook broccoli according to package; set aside.
Add chicken flavor to water and bring to a boil. Add onion and flour mixture. Stir well. Boil 5 minutes. Add broccoli; boil 3 more minutes. Take off heat. Add milk and salt and pepper.
Add water from cooking broccoli to soup for flavor.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Place in 4-quart ice cream churn.
Fill to line with milk.
Freeze according to directions for churn.

title: wassail
directions: Use a bag for cinnamon and cloves.
Mix ingredients in a 30-cup coffee maker; simmer an hour.
Remove cinnamon and cloves and serve.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve as dip with vegetables.

title: diet candy bar
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl until thick.
Shape onto waxed paper and freeze.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut shortening in and add buttermilk and yeast dissolved in warm water.
Work dough on floured board until smooth.
Refrigerate in greased bowl until ready for use.
Roll out dough and cut into biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mincemeat pie filling
directions: Stem and core apples and slice thin, then cut the slices into 8 to 10 pieces.
Cut the cooked roast beef into small pieces (like the apple).
Mix ingredients (except spices; add last) and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
You can keep longer.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter. Add sugar gradually and cream well. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition. Add flour alternately with milk (to which flavorings have been added).
Bake in Bundt pan (greased and floured) at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown chops; drain on paper.
In buttered 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange potatoes, mushrooms and the chops.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and drain well.
Heat oil in skillet; saute onions 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms; saute 2 minutes.
Stir in salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes. Stir in brandy.
Chill 3 hours.
Sprinkle with parsley just before serving.

title: cheesy mexican chicken 'n rice
directions: Spray a large skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Add chicken; cook and stir on medium-high heat 3 to 4 minutes or until cooked through. Reduce heat to medium-low. Add process cheese spread, corn, picante and seasonings.
Cook, stirring constantly, 1 or 2 minutes or until process cheese spread is completely melted. Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: homemade hash
directions: Brown hamburger and onion on medium heat; drain.
Add potatoes, garlic, salt and oil.
Mix good and cover.
Stir occasionally.
Turn on low heat until potatoes are tender, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: summer fruit dip
directions: Take mixer and blend Philadelphia cream cheese and marshmallow cream together until creamy.
It's the easiest, best tasting dip you'll ever try.

title: new orleans pralines
directions: Cook sugar and milk together for about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Beat well until mixture begins to cool. Add pecans.
Drop quickly onto wax paper.

title: green beans and onions
directions: Cook whole beans in boiling water for about 5 minutes.
Drain and run cold water over.
Put parsley, vinegar and mustard in bowl.
Add olive oil, salt and pepper, stirring rapidly with whisk.
Put beans in serving dish; garnish with onion rings. Spoon sauce over; toss lightly.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine all ingredients except pie shell.
Mix well and pour into pastry shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake for another 35 to 40 minutes.
Knife inserted near edge should come out clean when ready.
Cool.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown burger; precook carrots and celery.
Add tomatoes, 2 cups water and simmer.
Add rice, if desired.

title: 2 pecan pies
directions: Mix melted butter and box of sugar.
Add corn meal, water and eggs.
Stir in nuts and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine and pour over baked mixture.
Bake again for 25 - 30 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: corned beef hot dish
directions: Boil the Creamettes until tender.
Blanch, then mix with rest of ingredients.
Pour into casserole and top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach balls with mustard sauce
directions: Combine dry mustard and white vinegar.
Let set for 4 hours at room temperature.
Then mix sugar and egg yolk.
Cook and simmer over low heat.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes, but not real thin.
Wash and cook until slightly tender.
Drain potatoes and put into deep baking pan (about 5 to 6-inches).
In a heavy pan, put milk and butter and heat until real hot (making sure you don't scorch it), then add Cheddar cheese, stirring constantly to keep it from burning.
When cheese has melted, remove from the heat and mix up some cornstarch with cold water and add to the milk mixture.
Thicken to desired thickness by placing back on the heat.
Then pour over potatoes and place in heated oven at 400° and bake until the potatoes are finished cooking and brown on top.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook peeled and cubed eggplant in salted water until tender; mash and add remaining ingredients, except for the grated cheese. Pour into greased baking dish; sprinkle grated cheese over top. Bake 30 minutes or until brownish in color.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: In wok or skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add carrots and chicken. Stir fry for 1 minute.
Add eggs and pepper.
Stir fry for 1 minute.
Add rice and soy sauce.
Stir fry for 5 minutes. Garnish with scallions.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: casserole sauce mix
directions: Mix and store in an air tight container.
To Use:
Combine 1/3 cup mix and 1 cup water.
Cook and stir until thick.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan, put the pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Stir together.
Add the yellow cake mix (dry) and cut up the stick of butter or margarine and dot the top with it. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: eadie's frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and honey. Add strawberries, bananas, crushed pineapple and nuts.

title: floating pineapple cooler
directions: Put all the ingredients, except the cherry in a cocktail glass and stir well.
Add the cherry.

title: hot apple cereal
directions: Combine the milk, brown sugar, margarine, salt and cinnamon. Scald.
Combine the remaining ingredients in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or microwave 10 minutes at full power.
Stir several times.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Decrease baking powder to 2 teaspoons and add 1/4 teaspoon baking

title: cooked cranberry sauce
directions: Add the water to the cranberries and apples; boil them together.
Put them through a food mill and add sugar.
Fix according to your own taste.
Stir the mixture while it cools. Grate the orange rind, extract the juice from the oranges and add both to the mixture when it has cooled.

title: butterscotch crunch cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 baking sheets.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix oleo, 2 Tbsp. poppy seeds and crushed crackers.
Place in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2 inch dish.
Layer cut up chicken on top of crackers.
Mix soup, sour cream and 1 Tbsp. poppy seed in a bowl. Spread on top of chicken.
Top with 1 or 2 crushed crackers.
Bake 350° for 1 hour uncovered.
Can be served as is or on top of noodles.

title: corn dogs
directions: Put hot dogs in water and boil.
Drain on paper towels. Preheat vegetable oil in skillet.
Dip warm dogs in batter made from remaining ingredients.
Put into hot oil and brown.

title: marco island cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk, flour and vanilla. Make 1-inch balls.
With a fork, press down middle and then across.
Press a pecan into center.
Brush each cookie with a slightly beaten egg white.
Bake in 350° oven approximately 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken in 3 quarts water until cooked through.
Remove chicken, reserving broth. Cut chicken into bite size pieces. Discard skin and bones.
Set aside. Cook onion in margarine in skillet until tender; set aside.
Add enough water to broth to make 3 quarts. Bring to a boil.
Cook the vermicelli in broth until tender. Do not drain. Add Velveeta cheese. Cook until melted. Add tomatoes, mushrooms, onion and seasonings.
Pour into baking dishes.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly. This is very good cooked in a crock-pot also.

title: white chocolate macadamia nut cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugars. Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt together in a separate bowl.
Mix the two together.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Line a cookie sheet with a brown paper bag or parchment paper.
This will keep the cookies from "running" and being too thin (this is very important). Drop cookies by the teaspoonful onto paper.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 11 minutes.
Don't overcook.
No need to re-line pan with new paper for subsequent batches, just re-use paper.

title: spanish bean soup
directions: Start cooking ham bone or hock in 2 quarts water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat and simmer for 4 to 5 hours.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef with 1 teaspoon salt. Add kidney beans. Simmer 10 minutes.
Cool. Add rest of ingredients.
Garnish with avocado.

title: delicious apple cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients (flour, baking powder and salt); set aside.
Mix eggs, 2 cups sugar, orange juice, vanilla and oil, then mix with dry ingredients.
Peel apples, cut into small pieces for inside of cake.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
(Save some to sprinkle on top of cake when it is done.) Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: glazed almond salad
directions: Mix and shake well. Store ahead of time.
Shake before using.

title: quick and easy cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filing in 8 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle with dry cake mix.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach well; remove stems.
If leaves are big, tear up some.
Cook bacon; crumble.
Cube pears.
Mix the next 6 ingredients and refrigerate.
Do all this a day ahead if you like, but pour a little dressing over the pears.

title: country hush puppies
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a medium bowl; set aside. Combine egg and hot sauce; stir in buttermilk.
Pour into first seven dry ingredients, stirring just to mix.
Stir in onion and corn (do not overmix batter).
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls into deep, hot oil (350°); cook only a few at a time, turning once. Fry 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels. Yields 3 dozen.

title: southern dressing
directions: Crumble breads.
Add 3 cups boiling broth.
Cover; let stand 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: louisiana red beans and rice
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook until beans are done.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: chocolate roll
directions: About 1 hour ahead, set out eggs.
When ready to make cake, heat oven to 400°.
Grease waxed paper, then line bottom of jelly roll pan (paper-buttered side up).
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, cocoa and salt together 3 times.
Separate eggs.
Beat yolks and add flour mixture. Add vanilla.
Beat whites until stiff and fold into flour mixture.
Turn into pan.
Bake 12 minutes or just until cake springs back when gently touched.

title: pie delight
directions: Let jello set and beat with beater.
Add pineapple, rice and whipped cream; fold in.
Add sugar and vanilla to cream.

title: favorite yum-yum's
directions: Make a crust of margarine, flour, and nuts. Put in bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes; let cool. Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar, and 1 c. Cool Whip. Spread over cooled crust. Mix pudding and milk; when thickened, spread over the top. Cover all with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut and more nuts.

title: sour cream enchilada casserole
directions: Combine water and 2 tablespoons picante sauce in a large shallow dish.
Place tortillas in mixture; let stand 5 minutes and drain.
Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Stir in salt, pepper, cumin, chili powder, olives and 1/4 cup picante sauce; simmer meat mixture 5 minutes.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat and add sour cream.
Place 1/2 of tortillas in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Pour 1/2 of sour cream sauce over tortillas.
Spoon 1/2 of meat mixture over sauce.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese over meat mixture. Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Make white sauce of butter, flour and milk.
Slowly add small amount of sauce to eggs and stir into remaining sauce.
Add next four ingredients to mixture.
Fold egg whites into mixture.
Bake in casserole or individual baking dishes at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Mix chicken with cream of chicken and sour cream.
Mix crackers with butter and pour on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ten minute pecan squash
directions: Combine squash, butter, Tang, salt and pepper.
Cook as directed on package.
Stir in pecans.

title: kiki's trail mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt.
Add vinegar, egg and water.

title: deep dish butter cake
directions: Blend cake mix, butter and 2 eggs until smooth.
Spread into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch oven-safe pan.
Beat well the cream cheese, powdered sugar and remaining 2 eggs.
Spread on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° (325° for glass pans) for 35 minutes.

title: rosemary potatoes(when a baked potato won't do)
directions: Thoroughly clean potatoes; peel a 1-inch ring from the middle of the potatoes (only one strip).
Dip potatoes into oil, then place in baking pan.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon of onion and 1 teaspoon of dried rosemary on each potato.
Salt to taste.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Poke potato for doneness.
May need more time.

title: brownies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and eggs.
Melt butter. Cool and add flour and butter to sugar mixture, then add vanilla.
Mix and bake in 350° oven in 8-inch square pan for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch pie plate.
Beat eggs and blend in sugar and butter.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 1/2 c, white sugar with cinnamon. Set aside. Pull biscuits apart. Dip in margarine, roll in cinnamon and sugar. Layer in bunt pan over lapping biscuit half. Sprinkle some of the raisins, pecans and brown sugar over biscuits. Repeat layers until you have used all the biscuits.

title: creole seafood gumbo
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large, heavy pot or kettle.
Saute onion and garlic until lightly browned.
Add water, pepper, celery, okra, shrimp and rice.
Simmer gently for 30 to 40 minutes or until vegetables and shrimp are cooked.
Add tomatoes.
Blend flour, file powder or thyme, pepper sauce and Worcestershire sauce with clam juice.
Add to gumbo, stirring until smooth.
Add crabmeat and pimiento.
Taste for flavor; add additional seasonings if necessary.
Serve with additional cooked rice, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings with 148 calories per serving.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Grind up sausage and cook down with ground meat; drain.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 90 minutes.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Pour mix over crackers and stir.
Bake for 1 hour at 200°. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, milk, salt, cocoa and margarine.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
When smooth, stir in oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper lined pan. Yield: About 2 dozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350 until done.

title: grasshopper pie(very good)
directions: Combine chocolate crumbs and butter. Press in pie tin. Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 325° oven over low heat. Melt marshmallows and half and half. Cool mixtures. Add creme de menthe and creme de cacao. Fold in whipped cream and coloring, then pour mixture into pie shell. Sprinkle a few crumbs on top and chill.

title: basic bean recipe
directions: Add these ingredients and mix well.
Cover and cook over high heat until water is boiling.
This should bake 5 to 10 minutes. Lower heat and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes or until beans are completely tender and sauce has thickened somewhat.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, butter, lemon juice, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Spread on a pizza pan.
Layer lettuce, green onions, tomatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle on taco seasoning mix.
Serve with Doritos or Tostitos.

title: cornbread salad
directions: In bowl, crumble cornbread. Drain beans and spread over cornbread. Layer the remaining ingredients. Blend mayo and pickle juice. Spread on top. Refrigerate. Toss before serving.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix and spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Will be crumbly, spread 3/4 of crust in 9 x 12 pan.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add remaining ingredients and place into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake until done.
Remove when golden brown.

title: nick borren's noodles and mushrooms
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Add 1 tablespoon butter.
Add dash of salt.
Drain spaghetti.
Slice mushrooms; fry in second tablespoon of butter.
Pour mushrooms over spaghetti; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: pimiento rice
directions: Saute rice in butter for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring often until golden.
Stir in stock, onion and pimiento.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes until rice is tender and liquid absorbed.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot cranberry spice punch
directions: Bring cranberry juice cocktail, water and pineapple juice to a boil in a large saucepan.
Add ground spices.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Press 2 to 3 whole cloves into lemon slices.
Ladle punch into mugs; garnish with cinnamon stick (stirrer) and clove-studded lemon slice.
Drop pat of butter on top at last minute and serve immediately.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Mix butter and sugar and let cool.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and milk.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt and add to the mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen squares.

title: fresh strawberry glaze pie
directions: Mix together the sugar and cornstarch.
Add the warm water; cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add the jello; mix well. Cool.
Slice fresh strawberries in baked pie shell (as many as desired).
Pour glaze over strawberries.
Refrigerate.
Served with whipped topping.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and crumble.
Beat eggs.
Add all ingredients and mix together.
Refrigerate 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with fresh fruit and sweet rolls.

title: quick crunchies
directions: In small bowl, beat eggs well.
Stir in dates, margarine and sugar.
Pour into skillet.
Cook until thickened, stirring very often.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remainder.
Chill.
Form into balls.
Roll in coconut.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: peaches-n-cream pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine all crust ingredients; beat 2 minutes on medium speed. Pour into a greased deep-dish (9-inch) pie pan. Set aside briefly.

title: cold avocado soup
directions: In blender container place pitted and peeled avocado, broth, onion, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Puree on high about 10 seconds.
In medium bowl combine light and sour creams.
Blend avocado mixture into cream mixture.
Chill.
Serve in chilled bowls garnished with a thin lemon slice or sprinkling of paprika.

title: pecan balls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and shape into small balls.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Chill.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: crabmeat salad
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Combine with cheese, soup, mayonnaise, onion, salt and Worcestershire sauce in medium saucepan, heating carefully until well blended.
Remove from heat. Add crabmeat and celery.
Pour into mold and chill until firm. Serve on lettuce.

title: butter nut chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, vanilla and margarine until creamy.
Add salt, baking powder and flour.
Beat on low speed until well mixed.
Add nuts and spread in prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until top is light brown.
Don't overbake!
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes two dozen.

title: sun gold coconut cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar to a smooth cream.
Stir in the well beaten egg yolks and beat until very light.
Sift dry ingredients together 3 times and add alternately with milk to first mixture. Add vanilla and carefully fold in egg whites which have been beaten to a stiff froth.
Bake in layers in a moderate oven (350°).
Put together with coconut cream icing.
Makes a large cake.

title: remarkable fudge
directions: Cook
first
3 ingredients, stirring often, to slightly firm ball stage.
If you have a heavy pan it would help.
This sticks very
easily.
Add	Marshmallow
Creme,
vanilla
and chocolate chips.
Stir
quickly
until well blended.	Add nut meats.	Pour quickly
into
buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let it get firm
and cut in squares.
This makes a large quantity and is nice and creamy.

title: special cornstarch meringue(for 3 egg whites)
directions: Moisten cornstarch with small amount of cold water.
Stir in boiling water.
Cook until thick and clear.

title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Drain liquid from 1 jar artichoke hearts into a frying pan. Drain liquid from other jar and save for other uses.

title: warm brie with apples and almonds
directions: Place Brie on ovenproof serving dish and warm in 300° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Melt butter and saute almonds until golden.
Remove Brie and pour butter/almond mix over it.
Serve with crackers, baguette and sliced cold apples.
Serves 4.

title: beef 'n bean barbecue bake
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add beans, sauce, onion and salt. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/4 pound process cheese spread cubes.
Pour into baking dish.
Place biscuits on top of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In large pot, combine all ingredients.
If desired, may add chopped green pepper, more onion and chopped mushrooms near end of cooking time.
Simmer on stove 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: squmpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, salt and spices into a bowl; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in another bowl; blend well, using rotary beater.
Add pumpkin mixture all at once to dry ingredients, stirring just enough to moisten.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Test with toothpick or cake tester to make sure bread is done.
Remove from pan; cool completely.

title: curried chicken-grape salad
directions: Toss
chicken, mayonnaise mixed with curry powder, salt and grapes
in	a medium size bowl.
Sprinkle with cashews or peanuts and serve with a cluster of grapes and pita bread.

title: never fail yeast biscuits
directions: Mix together warm water, yeast and sugar; when yeast dissolves add oil, buttermilk and baking soda, mix well. Add flour.
Put in a covered bowl for a few hours or overnight.
Stir, put on floured board and work with hands to form a biscuit.
Bake at 450 degrees for 10-12 minutes or until brown.
Can be kept up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: hoecakes
directions: Sift flour and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and knead. Drop by teaspoonfuls on hot greased griddle.
Brown on both sides and turn to finish browning.
Makes 10 cakes or using 8-inch iron skillet, greased and hot, spread mixture in skillet.
Brown on both sides.
Cut into pie size serving to serve.

title: polish lasagna(pierogi casserole)
directions: Cook potatoes.
Mash with 3 tablespoons margarine.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Saute onions with remaining margarine and set aside 1/2 of the sauteed onions.
Add sauerkraut to other 1/2 of sauteed onions.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Add water, if needed, to prevent burning.

title: stuffed vidalia onion
directions: Place a piece of plastic wrap large enough to cover stuffed onion in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Slice onion crosswise into 3 layers.
Place bottom slice of onion on plastic wrap.
Place butter in a 4-cup glass measure; microwave at High 20 seconds to melt.
Stir in salt, pepper, stuffing mix and beef broth.
Place a little less than 1/2 of the stuffing mixture on onion slice in casserole.
Add center slice of onion.
Top with most of remaining stuffing mixture, reserving 1 tablespoon.
Top mixture with third onion slice.
Spread remaining stuffing mixture over onion; pull up corners of plastic wrap and tie with string.
Microwave at High 6 minutes.
Let stand 6 to 8 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli salad supreme
directions: Toss together all vegetables, bacon, nuts, and grapes. Mix sugar, mayonnaise, and vinegar to make a dressing. Pour dressing over mixture; stir gently to coat evenly. Refrigerate overnight before serving, to allow flavors to mix.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Brown sugar; add syrup and peanuts and cook until nuts turn brown.
Take off heat and stir in salt and soda.
Pour in pan and let cool.
When cooled, break in pieces.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes for 45 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together. Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mud-foo-ni cabbage and rice
directions: Saute meat and onion in hot oil.
Add cabbage, rice and seasoning.
Stir about 5 minutes.
Add 5 1/2 cups water.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Cook over medium heat 1/2 hour stirring occasionally.
Add tomato sauce and cook over low heat about 20 minutes or until most of liquid has evaporated and porridge looks like cooked rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 1/4 cups cold water.
Add pineapple to jello.
Slice bananas on top.
Place marshmallows on top of bananas.
Chill until set.

title: hobo dinner for two
directions: Make 2 big patties of hamburger, adding salt and pepper to mixture.
Slice equal amounts of vegetables and put on top of hamburger buns.
Wrap in heavy aluminum foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: one-half pound cake
directions: Add sugar to butter and cream until fluffy.
Add eggs, flour and any flavoring.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender (may need more water). Take chicken out and set aside to cool.
Take out 1 cup broth and set aside.
Now add can of broth, cream and food coloring to remaining broth.
Mix reserved broth and flour.
Roll dough fairly thin.
