Slice or tear off pieces of dough and drop into boiling broth.
Take chicken off bone and put back in dumplings. Simmer for a few minutes until dumplings are done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: tuna carrot salad
directions: Combine tuna, carrots, celery and onion in bowl and set aside. Mix together mayonnaise, milk, mustard and pepper.
Add to tuna mixture; toss gently.
Cover and chill until serving time.
Add La Choy chow mein noodles.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Beat with electric mixer until creamy.
Good served plain or rolled in crushed nuts, fresh parsley or bacon bits.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: southern oven salmon
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Line baking sheet with foil; grease foil well. Generously oil salmon skin.
Place fish skin side down on foil.
Remove bones, if any.
Season with salt and pepper. Combine parsley and green onions; spread over salmon.
Cover with lemon slices.
Bake 15 minutes.
Remove lemon slices and scrape off loose parsley.
Serve with mounds of rice pilaf and spoon cucumbers down center of each salmon piece.

title: oven baked french fries
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 1/-8 inch wedges lengthwise.
Set aside.
Mix together oil and the rest of the ingredients.
Add the potatoes and coat well.
Place in a single layer on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Rinse and sort beans in cold water.
Pull out all rocks and bad beans.
Drain.
Put about 2 quarts cold water into pot.
Be sure beans are well covered and have enough liquid.
Cover and heat for about 1 minute.
Remove from heat and let soak for at least one hour (the longer, the better).
Bring beans to full boil.
Add ham bone, onion, garlic, parsley flakes and celery. Simmer for about 2 hours.
Add salt and pepper (never before because salt will harden the beans).
Mash a few beans in a spoon and stir in to thicken the gravy.
Let simmer for 15 minutes more. Serve over rice with French bread and cold beer.

title: reese's cookies
directions: Cream shortening or margarine, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour and baking soda.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add spices, tomatoes and olives.
Halve corn tortillas and microwave 1 minute.
Mix egg and Ricotta cheese.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer meat, Ricotta cheese, Monterey Jack cheese and tortillas.
Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli by directions on package.
Cook rice according to directions on box.
Add rice, broccoli and soup in a casserole dish with minced onion.
Mix well.
Melt butter in skillet.
Cut bread in cubes and fry in butter.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: soft boiled fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Cover and cook until boiling point is reached.
Boil to soft ball stage.
Add flavoring.
Cool without stirring to room temperature.
Beat until mixture is creamy and thick and will hold its shape when dropped from a teaspoon.
Pour into well-buttered shallow pan.

title: fried potato cakes
directions: Add melted butter and beaten egg to mashed potatoes.
Mix in enough flour as needed to make a soft dough. Drop by heaping spoonfuls into a buttered pan.
Flatten to 1/2-inch thickness. Fry until light brown.

title: rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into small muffin pan.
Leave tops of muffins uneven.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Place rice on bottom of greased casserole.
Sprinkle soup mix on rice.
Add water.
Put chicken parts on rice.
Pour on cream of chicken soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: yum plum cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: chicken alouette
directions: Roll pastry on floured surface to 12 x 14-inch.
Cut into 4 sections.
Trim small amount off corners to make ovals and set aside for trim.
Spread with Alouette cheese to within 1-inch of edge.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper and place on ovals. Moisten edges with water.
Fold ends and then sides; press to seal.
Place seam side down on lightly greased (or sprayed) baking sheet.
Repeat with remaining pastry sheet.
Garnish chicken bundles with reserved pastry trimmings.
Cover and refrigerate up to 2 hours.
Combine egg and water.
Brush over pastry bundles. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix gelatin and boiling water until partially set.
Then add fruit.

title: irish coffee
directions: Warm a stemmed whiskey glass.
Put in the sugar and enough hot coffee to dissolve it.
Stir well.
Add Irish whiskey to fill within an inch of the brim.
Now for the tricky part:
Hold a teaspoon curved-side up across the glass and pour the cold cream slowly over the spoon.
Do not stir the cream into the coffee.
It should float on top and the hot whiskey-laced coffee is drunk through the cold cream.
Slainte!

title: sausage pasta rolls
directions: Remove casing from sausage; crumble and brown in skillet. Drain. Add onion; stir in 1/2 cup sauce and 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese. Cover each noodle with sausage mixture; roll up. Place seam side down in baking dish. Spoon remaining mixture over noodles. Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Soften butter or margarine; gradually add sugar.
Add the eggs and beat thoroughly.
Stir in the bananas and vanilla extract.
In a separate bowl sift together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Add half the flour to the banana mixture.
Stir, then add half the milk or sour cream.
Add remaining flour; stir, then the milk.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Whip the butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, until
creamy.
Add
vanilla.
Add
flour while mixer is running. Pour cake
mix
in
pan
and
cook for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 250°.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook hamburger until done and drain.
Add all remaining ingredients to hamburger.
Let cook until you cook your yellow cornmeal; mush.
Mix 5 cups boiling water, 1 cup tomato juice, a little cayenne pepper, and a little salt.
Add 2 cups yellow cornmeal, stirring slowly constantly until thick.
Line a 3-quart casserole dish with corn mush, it will be thick, then pour all in skillet.
Then put the rest of meal on top.
Bake, uncovered, in oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: sissies chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Then fold in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: company rice
directions: Combine and stir in casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 400° for one hour.
Remove lid last 15 minutes to brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barb's sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350°.

title: cinnamon chips
directions: One portion at each meal.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble corn bread very fine. Add other ingredients, adding mayonnaise last. Dilute the mayo with small amount of water or milk to make thinner consistency. When all is thoroughly mixed, refrigerate to chill before serving. Garnish with cooked and crumbled bacon.

title: dill pickles
directions: Heat water, vinegar, sugar and salt to boiling.
Put cleaned cukes into liquid; when they start to turn white, pack into jars which have dill, garlic and 1/2 teaspoon alum in them.
Pour hot liquid over the cukes and seal.

title: cream candy
directions: Pour water over sugar, add salt and soda.
Slowly add cream after it boils well, add butter.
Cook until it hardens in cold water pour on cool platter and pull until it creams.

title: chinese egg foo young
directions: In a bowl, mix water, mixed vegetables, green onions and soy sauce.
Beat eggs and add to vegetable mixture.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and 1/3 cup butter in bowl, mixing well. Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and remaining 1/3 cup butter together in bowl.
Sprinkle over sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until browned.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: night before casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make three holes in dry ingredients.
First hole, add oil; second, add vinegar and third, vanilla.
Add water to all and mix well.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Pack firmly in buttered loaf pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn out on platter; garnish with boiled eggs and cover with cream soup of choice (slightly thinned).
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.
Mix well with wire whisk.
Set aside.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix brown sugar and oil. Add egg, buttermilk, vanilla and rhubarb. Add dry ingredients and nuts. Divide batter equally between 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cranberry-apple relish
directions: Wash all fruit.
Pare and core apples.
Cut oranges and lemon. Put all through coarse blade food chopper.
Add sugar and honey. Refrigerate until cold.
Good with turkey and chicken.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least 8 hours. Serve with chips.

title: easy pudding
directions: Beat pie filling, milk and crushed pineapple together.
Fold in whipped topping.

title: coconut cake
directions: Pour cake mix into large bowl. Add pudding mix, eggs, oil and water. Beat with electric mixer for 4 minutes. Pour into two 9-inch layer pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool. Frost with icing. Cover generously with coconut.
tags: cream of coconut instant pudding mix

title: squash-peach bake
directions: Salt squash lightly.
In a greased 2-quart baking dish, arrange squash and peaches in alternate layers.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar; dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until squash is tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix molasses and sugar with oil; add egg.
Mix thoroughly. Sift together flour, cream of tartar, spices and salt.
Dissolve soda in hot water and add to first mixture.
Add vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients all at once.
Chill for 1 hour or more. Roll dough and cut out cookies.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat, drain and add garlic, oregano, 1/2 teaspoon salt; simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and paste.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 10 to 15 minutes.
Boil noodles for 5 minutes.
Drain and chill in cold water.
Mix eggs, cottage cheese, parsley and pepper.
Blend well.

title: apples with cream
directions: Peel, core and quarter the apples.
Place in a baking dish. Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with sugar and pour cream over all. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until soft.
Serve warm. This is a good brunch dish or easy dessert.

title: freezer salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Boil one minute.
Cool.

title: fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into molds or into a long dish.
Chill and serve.

title: party chicken
directions: Put bacon strips around breasts.
Mix 3 or 4 cans cream of mushroom soup and large carton of sour cream.
Pour over chicken and add chipped beef.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: lemon jack jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O according to package.
Add drained pineapple, bananas (sliced) and marshmallows.
Set until firm in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: brunch casserole
directions: In a large bowl, toss the bread and cheese cubes together. Add the other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 inch sq. baking dish and cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight. When ready to bake, leave the foil on and place in a 350° over for 1 hour.

title: coconut candy bar cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Microwave squares of chocolate and 1/2 cup margarine in large bowl at High for 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate until blended.
Blend in eggs, one at a time, with electric mixer on low speed until completely mixed.
Add vanilla. Stir in 1/3 cup flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat in remaining flour alternately with water until well blended and smooth.

title: cooking for a crowd fiesta cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until dry ingredients are dampened.
Divide evenly between 2 greased 9 x 13-inch baking pans.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 24.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour box of rice into pan, such as a cake pan.
Mix cream of chicken soup in a bowl; mix up good and pour over rice; mix good.
Put cut-up chicken on top of rice.
Put melted butter on the chicken pieces.
Bake 1 hour uncovered and brown chicken for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter.
Add rice to beef broth and consomme.
Pour in butter and onions and season to taste.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: danish cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into julienne strips.
Melt butter in large skillet or electric frypan.
Add cabbage and other ingredients.
Cook until liquid is absorbed and cabbage is tender.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Cook pumpkin.
Wash and cut in half crosswise.
Remove seeds and strings.
Place it in a pan, shell side up, and bake at 325° for 1 hour or more, depending on size, until it is tender and begins to fall apart.
Scrape the pulp from the shell and put it through a ricer, strainer or blender.

title: diabetic chocolate chip mint cream pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, milk, flavoring and food coloring in a saucepan.
Stir to dissolve pudding mix.
Cook and stir over medium heat until a full boil.
Set aside and let cool.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour in pastry shell.
Refrigerate until cool.
Decorate with whipped topping.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, water, salt mincemeat, and lard together.
Add flour and soda to mixture and stir well.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Mix all together, cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: In 2-quart greased casserole dish, place bottom crust. Bake until brown. Boil vegetables until tender; drain. Mix vegetables and chicken with soup. Pour over crust. Place top crust on top of casserole. Bake at 385° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: refried beans
directions: Put shortening in skillet.
Add beans, one cup at a time, mashing after each addition.
Add tomatoes and mash them, then the picante sauce.
Taste for salt.

title: holiday party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pitcher and chill.
Serve over ice cubes.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into balls, then flatten with fork.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: effie's potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients, except milk, cheese and bacon, into a large Dutch oven (or any sort of cooker or kettle).
Cover and cook on low heat until very tender; then blend with a potato masher or run through a blender.
Add the milk and just heat a bit.

title: lillian's carrot cake
directions: Blend together oil, eggs, sugar, carrots and walnuts; set aside.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix together sifted ingredients with other mixture that was set aside. Blend all together well.
Bake in a greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: oatmeal spice cake
directions: Boil water and pour over oats.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Combine sugar, eggs and shortening, mixing well.
In separate bowl combine dry ingredients.
Add oat mixture to sugar mixture.
Fold in dry ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cake may be served with icing or whipped cream, but is good enough just by itself!

title: broccoli bread
directions: Cook broccoli a little.
Squeeze out all water.
Mix other ingredients.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan or make muffins. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Break apart rice noodles and deep fry in 2 to 3-inches hot vegetable or soy oil, above 350°.
Noodles will fry within seconds and will be white and crisp when done.
Larger quantities may be fried in batches.
Drain and set aside.

title: impossible pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in blender for 10 seconds.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into buttered deep dish pie plate.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine and toss with dressing.

title: marriage stew
directions: Combine the 2 concerned persons with the 2 cups of love in an adequate, comfortable mixing area.
Next, blend in the understanding and patience and beat lightly with a spoon made of laughter until the mixture is smooth and fluffy.
Now, add the 2 cans of trust and pour the mixture into the casserole of life and place over very low heat to simmer.
This is also the time to add tears, dreams, touching, remembering and any other spices you feel will make your stew more exciting.
As the mixture is simmering, saute the sex in tenderness and perhaps a little wine on special occasions.
Add this to the main casserole until desired strength is reached.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Rinse chicken, pat dry.
Place each breast between 2 pieces of wax paper.
Working from center to edges, lightly pound with the flat side of a meat mallet to 1/8 inch thickness.
Place 1 slice each of ham and cheese on chicken, folding to fit if necessary.
Starting from the short side, roll up jelly roll style and secure with a toothpick.
In a shallow dish, stir beaten eggs and 2 Tbsp. wine or broth.
Roll each breast in flour, dip in egg mixture and coat with breadcrumbs.
Preheat oven to 325°.
In skillet, melt butter; lightly brown chicken rolls on all sides. Remove from skillet and transfer to a 9 x 13 inch ovenproof dish. Reserve drippings.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.

title: rice dressing
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage, onion and bell pepper. Drain. Put in casserole dish. Add soups and rice. Stir well. Cover and bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Uncover and bake another 20 minutes.

title: good icing for angel cake
directions: Mix together pudding, milk and powdered sugar.
Beat 1 minute with mixer.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well.

title: molasses squares
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add molasses, egg, cloves, cinnamon and flour.
Dissolve soda in water; add to bowl.
Add raisins; mix well.
Spread on cookie sheet; sprinkle with sugar. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix the sugar, salt and flour.
Add butter and cream until smooth.
Add beaten eggs and continue beating.
Add syrup and vanilla, then nuts.
Pour into pie shell and bake until firm in center.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cheese balls
directions: Grate Cheddar cheeses and mix with cream cheese and nuts.
Form into balls.
Roll in nuts.
Chill before slicing.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach as directed on the package.
Saute the onion in margarine.
Mix spinach and onion in a large bowl.
Add eggs, cheese and stuffing mix.
Season to taste.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems; chop stems.
Fry Parks sausage; drain.
In a bowl, mix stems, sausage and diced Mozzarella.
Add grated cheese, parsley and bread crumbs; toss. Fill caps.
Drizzle oil on them.
Bake in preheated oven for 20 minutes to 1/2 hour.

title: cranberry crunch molded salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add cold water and lemon juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place mixture in 2-quart mold.
Chill until firm. Unmold just before serving.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter and flour, in small bowl. In small skillet, melt butter and add flour.
Then add mixture in small bowl and stir until thickened.
Put in cooked hamburger or cut-up roast and serve on hamburger buns (1 1/2 pounds meat or leftover roast).

title: lemon refrigerator dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O, water, sugar and juice.
When syrupy from chilling, add whipped cream, folding until smooth.
Fold in angel food cake (pieces no bigger than 50 cent pieces).
Chill.
Can be made on the same day served, or the day before and let set up in refrigerator.
Should be fluffy.

title: lemon-lime tropical mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup syrup.
Dissolve lime jello in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until partially set; fold in pineapple and nuts.
Pour into oiled 1 1/2-quart mold (or non-oiled Tupperware mold) until almost set.

title: chicken and peanuts
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces and place in a 3-quart round casserole.
Combine wine, soy sauce, cornstarch, water, ginger and garlic and pour over chicken.
Cover and microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir.
Add green pepper and microwave, covered, on High for 5 more minutes.
Stir in peanuts and let stand 3 to 4 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine the cranberries and sugar; let set overnight. Add the orange, apples, walnuts and marshmallows. Mix well. Let sit for at least 4 hours.

title: peas, rice and ham salad
directions: In large bowl, combine cooked peas, rice, pimiento, peppers, ham and onions.
Pour dressing over all and toss thoroughly. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: kentucky corn bread
directions: Grease and flour Pyrex dish or iron skillet and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup sugar.
Add flour.
Add egg yolks, water, vinegar and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in uncooked pie shell.
Cover with meringue made with whites of egg and remaining sugar.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine ingredients and add a little salt.
Place in a pie shell and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: chili dip
directions: Smooth cream cheese in 8 x 8 baking dish.
Pour can of chili on cream cheese.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.	 Place in oven at 350° for about 10 minutes or until warm and cheese is melted. Serve with chips for dipping.

title: raggedy ann cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box and cool.
Divide cake into thirds.
In a large (approximately 8-quart) bowl, crumble 1/3 of the cake.
Mix chocolate pudding as directed on box and layer over cake.
Layer nuts over pudding.
Take another 1/3 of the cake and crumble over nuts and pudding.
Mix vanilla pudding as directed on box and layer over cake. Drain pineapple and layer over pudding. Crumble remaining cake over pudding and pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Allow to chill and serve.

title: dutch oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and shortening.
Let cool. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: quick new england clam chowder
directions: Stir-fry onions in 2 tablespoons butter in large saucepan over moderate heat 5 to 8 minutes. Drain liquid from clams into pan. Add potatoes, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer until potatoes are nearly tender. Add clams, milk and cream. Cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes, just to heat through. Add remaining butter and stir until melted.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.

title: chicken divan
directions: Simmer chicken in water to cover for 25 minutes.
Skin and bone cooked chicken.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Melt butter, stir in flour and cook until bubbly.
Add broth and Worcestershire sauce; cook, stirring until thickened.
Reduce heat and stir in 1 cup of cheese until melted.
Empty sour cream into medium bowl; gradually add cheese sauce, stirring constantly.
Add soup and stir.
Arrange broccoli in 8 portions in baking dish.
Top each with half a chicken breast, pour sauce over all.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt, water and cream of tartar.
Cook until mixture comes away from side of pan.
Cool.
Knead out lumps. Divide into several balls.
Knead a different food coloring into each ball.
Cool for children to handle.
Store tightly covered. Have fun.

title: avocado salad
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, peel avocados and discard pits.
Cut avocados and tomatoes into bite size chunks.
Cut peel from oranges.
Cut oranges crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices. In a bowl, gently toss avocados, tomatoes, orange slices, black beans, cilantro and salt.
Makes 4 accompaniment servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix tuna and soup.
Then add peas.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle potato chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until bubbly and brown.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add Beef Tonight, lasagna flavor, and let simmer while cooking lasagna noodles.
Pour enough sauce and ground beef mixture in casserole dish to cover bottom. Put layer of cooked lasagna.
Mix Mozzarella cheese and cottage cheese.
Add layer to casserole.
Add another layer of each.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: italian tangerine ice
directions: Combine sugar, peel, gelatin and water in saucepan.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Boil 3 minutes; cool.
Add tangerine juice and pulp, orange and lemon juices.
Press through sieve, then freeze in tray until mixture is snowy and frothy.
Serve in tall glasses.
Good for a hot summer day.

title: roquefort spread
directions: Soften cheeses and blend together.

title: corn bread
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in pan and mix ingredients. Pour in pan. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; mix well and pour into a greased 9 x 13 baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheet and drop with a spoon.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage bread
directions: Fry sausage, peppers and onions, then drain it.
Roll out dough to fit the cookie sheet; spread melted butter on top.
Spread sausage, peppers and onions on top, then sprinkle with cheese. Roll it up like a jelly roll, large side first.
Place the seam on the bottom, then brush with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Coat roasting pan with cooking spray.
Mix crumbs, parsley, salt and peppers in bowl.
Brush chicken with melted butter.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Put in pan and bake 24 minutes.
Turn chicken over and bake 20 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut meat into thin strips, 3 to 4 inches long and 1 inch wide. Heat oil in skillet and brown meat.
Pour off fat.
Add drained pineapple.

title: pineapple chicken in patty shells
directions: Prepare patty shells according to package directions.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Fry bacon until done.
Shred cabbage with a knife.
Wash cabbage before you shred it.
Add 1/3 cup or less of water.
Add cabbage.
Cook until they come to a fry.
Stir so they don't stick.
They are done when cabbage is tender.

title: shirley's apple crisp
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the butter. Pour into dish (that has a cover) and dot with butter. Bake at 350° in a buttered and covered dish for 1 hour.

title: tomato, rice and bean casserole
directions: Saut pepper, onion and celery in oil until very lightly browned.
Chop tomatoes and add with chili powder to sauted vegetables.
Mix together rice and beans in a separate bowl.
Layer in a 9 x 13 glass dish half rice mixture, half grated cheese and half of tomato mixture.
Repeat.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Drain peas and corn.
Layer noodles, peas, corn and tuna. Pour soup over layers.
Strip with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 320°.

title: chicken ala ellyn
directions: Pound each breast flat.
Pat with flour and fry in oil until golden brown.
Place on cookie sheet.
Top each breast with 1 slice of ham, 1 ring of pineapple and 1 slice of cheese (in that order).
Bake at 350° until cheese is hot and bubbly and slightly browned, about 15 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place chicken in single layer in greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spoon sauerkraut over chicken.
Arrange cheese over sauerkraut.
Pour dressing over top. Cover pan and bake about 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Sprinkle coconut and pecans on bottom of oblong cake pan which has been lightly greased.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
Melt margarine.
Beat cream cheese in margarine.
(Do not have margarine too hot.)
Beat in sugar.
Pour over cake and bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hot baked chicken salad
directions: Cook and chop chicken.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in baking dish.
Cover top with cracker crumbs or crushed potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit dressing
directions: Combine sugar
and
flour.
Add juice and cook over low heat until
mixture
thickens.
Add
butter
and egg yolks and cook 3 minutes.
Chill
at
least 2 hours before serving.	To serve, pour over diced apples, mandarin oranges, pineapple and bananas.

title: steak marinade
directions: I double all the ingredients and mix with a mixer.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Cook sausage until done and mix all remaining ingredients together.
Roll into small balls. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
You can freeze and reheat when ready to serve.

title: cookie mix
directions: In
large bowl (10 quart) combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Stir
in
nuts
and
chocolate
chips (etc.). Store in	airtight container in a cool place or freezer for up to 3 months.

title: seafood pate
directions: Put equal amounts of shrimp and crab in food processor. Process until chopped fine; moisten with mayonnaise until it holds together.
Season with salt, pepper and dill and a little cocktail sauce.
Put in loaf pan coated with cocktail sauce. Chill.
Turn out on a plate.
Cover with the cocktail sauce. Serve with crackers.
(Use a fish mold, if possible.)

title: forgotten torte
directions: Butter bottom (not sides) of an angel food cake pan.
Set oven to 450°.
In large mixing bowl, whip egg whites, salt and cream of tartar until frothy.
Add 2 tablespoons of sugar at a time, beating well after each.
Add extracts.
Beat until glossy and forms stiff peaks.
Spread in pan.
Turn off oven and put pan in oven overnight.
Next day, carefully remove from pan.
Run knife around edge of the pan.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, add whipped cream or Cool Whip and serve with strawberries or fruit in season.
This is custard-like.

title: peanut pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, corn syrup and butter.
Spread peanuts in pie shell.
Pour filling over top.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool well before cutting into wedges.

title: grandma's feather dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg, melted butter and enough milk to moisten stiff batter.
Boil chicken pieces and then take out of broth.
Drop dumplings by teaspoon into boiling liquid.
Cook covered and without peeking for 18 minutes or until dumplings are done.
Take bones out of chicken and then add chicken back in broth with dumplings.

title: tortilla huevos con salsa
directions: Cut tortillas into strips, about 1/2 x 1 1/2-inches.
Crisp in oil in a frying pan with onion and garlic.
Precook pepper and mushrooms in a covered saucepan in a teaspoon of oil until tender. Low heat for 5 minutes.
Add pepper and mushrooms to tortillas and onion in frypan.
Mix well, then add eggs, folding until eggs are dry.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Heat salsa in saucepan. Serve with hot salsa spooned over top.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs with fork; stir in sugar, melted butter, lemon juice, vanilla and coconut.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Grease square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Cook and stir ground beef until brown. Drain.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, cheese and onion.
Reserve. Mix Bisquick and water until soft dough forms.
Pat in pan, pressing dough 1/2-inch up sides.
Layer beef, tomatoes and green pepper in pan.
Spoon sour cream mixture over top.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired. Bake at 375° until edges of dough are light brown (25 to 30 minutes).

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Spray a 6-cup fluted cake pan with nonstick cooking spray. In a large mixing bowl, beat the sugar and margarine until smooth and fluffy.
Beat in sour cream, egg whites, lemon rind and lemon juice until smooth.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt and add to batter.
Mix until smooth, about 1 minute.
Spoon batter into prepared pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan on wire rack 20 minutes.
Invert onto wire rack.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and milk.
Mix with chopped chicken.
Can double for 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine butter and crackers. Spread over chicken mixture.
Sprinkle poppy seed over mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: hamburger on french bread
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and then spread on each half of the split bread.
Put foil around bread to keep it from getting too dry.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: tuna and eggplant skillet
directions: In a large skillet, cook eggplant, onions, and peppers in butter. Cook until tender crisp. Add mushroom soup, tuna, 1 c. cheese, seasonings, and rice. Heat thoroughly. Top with remaining cheese. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired. Cover and heat until cheese melts. Serve with celery and carrot sticks.

title: black devil's food cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and baking soda together.
Add oil and buttermilk and stir until well blended.
Bring to boil the coffee; stir gently into batter (instant coffee can be used). Mixture will be soupy.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(This is low in cholesterol because of the cocoa, oil and buttermilk.)

title: russian chicken
directions: Wash chicken and arrange in a baking dish.
In a pan on medium heat, mix together the preserves, dressing and onion soup mix until mixture starts to boil.
Remove from heat and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon dipped blueberry muffins
directions: Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of the mixture.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir just until mixed.
Set aside.
Toss blueberries with 2 tablespoons of sugar and lemon rind.
Fold into batter.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan.
Combine melted butter and lemon juice.
Dip warm muffins in this mixture, then into sugar.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: good and easy vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except pepper sauce and bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat and simmer for about 15 minutes.
Stir in pepper sauce.

title: bacon strata
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Reserve 4 tablespoons of drippings.
Use 1 tablespoon to grease bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook onion and mushrooms in remaining drippings until tender.
Arrange bread in dish.
Top with mushroom mixture, cheese and crumbled bacon.
Mix eggs, milk and salt. Pour over bacon; refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.
Serves 6.
Great breakfast when you have "house guests."
Serve with Bloody Marys and fresh fruit.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Pour sweetened condensed milk and Reese's peanut butter chips in saucepan. Cook on low heat until melted.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour onto wax paper.
Refrigerate until firm.
